15/*
16 OpenGL backend. Binding vertex attribute locations and decomposing uniform
17 buffers into uniforms are handled transparently to the application via the
18 reflection data (QShaderDescription). Real uniform buffers are never used,
19 regardless of the GLSL version. Textures and buffers feature no special
20 logic, it's all just glTexSubImage2D and glBufferSubData (with "dynamic"
21 buffers set to GL_DYNAMIC_DRAW). The swapchain and the associated
22 renderbuffer for depth-stencil will be dummies since we have no control over
23 the underlying buffers here. While the baseline here is plain GLES 2.0, some
24 modern GL(ES) features like multisample renderbuffers, blits, and compute are
25 used when available. Also functional with core profile contexts.
26*/
27
28/*!
29 \class QRhiGles2InitParams
30 \internal
31 \inmodule QtGui
32 \brief OpenGL specific initialization parameters.
33
34 An OpenGL-based QRhi needs an already created QSurface that can be used in
35 combination with QOpenGLContext. Most commonly, this is a QOffscreenSurface
36 in practice. Additionally, while optional, it is recommended that the QWindow
37 the first QRhiSwapChain will target is passed in as well.
38
39 \badcode
40 QOffscreenSurface *fallbackSurface = QRhiGles2InitParams::newFallbackSurface();
41 QRhiGles2InitParams params;
42 params.fallbackSurface = fallbackSurface;
43 params.window = window;
44 rhi = QRhi::create(QRhi::OpenGLES2, &params);
45 \endcode
46
47 By default QRhi creates a QOpenGLContext on its own. This approach works
48 well in most cases, included threaded scenarios, where there is a dedicated
49 QRhi for each rendering thread. As there will be a QOpenGLContext for each
50 QRhi, the OpenGL context requirements (a context can only be current on one
51 thread) are satisfied. The implicitly created context is destroyed
52 automatically together with the QRhi.
53
54 The QSurfaceFormat for the context is specified in \l format. The
55 constructor sets this to QSurfaceFormat::defaultFormat() so applications
56 that call QSurfaceFormat::setDefaultFormat() with the appropriate settings
57 before the constructor runs will not need to change value of \l format.
58
59 \note Remember to set the depth and stencil buffer sizes to 24 and 8 when
60 the renderer relies on depth or stencil testing, either in the global
61 default QSurfaceFormat, or, alternatively, separately in all the involved
62 QSurfaceFormat instances: in \l format, the format argument passed to
63 newFallbackSurface(), and on any QWindow that is used with the QRhi.
64
65 A QSurface has to be specified in \l fallbackSurface. In order to prevent
66 mistakes in threaded situations, this is never created automatically by the
67 QRhi because, like QWindow, instances of QSurface subclasses can often be
68 created on the gui/main thread only.
69
70 As a convenience, applications can use newFallbackSurface() which creates
71 and returns a QOffscreenSurface that is compatible with the QOpenGLContext
72 that is going to be created by the QRhi afterwards. Note that the ownership
73 of the returned QOffscreenSurface is transferred to the caller and the QRhi
74 will not destroy it.
75
76 \note With the OpenGL backend, QRhiSwapChain can only target QWindow
77 instances that have their surface type set to QSurface::OpenGLSurface or
78 QSurface::RasterGLSurface.
79
80 \note \l window is optional. It is recommended to specify it whenever
81 possible, in order to avoid problems on multi-adapter and multi-screen
82 systems. When \l window is not set, the very first
83 QOpenGLContext::makeCurrent() happens with \l fallbackSurface which may be
84 an invisible window on some platforms (for example, Windows) and that may
85 trigger unexpected problems in some cases.
86
87 In case resource sharing with an existing QOpenGLContext is desired, \l
88 shareContext can be set to an existing QOpenGLContext. Alternatively,
89 Qt::AA_ShareOpenGLContexts is honored as well, when enabled.
90
91 \section2 Working with existing OpenGL contexts
92
93 When interoperating with another graphics engine, it may be necessary to
94 get a QRhi instance that uses the same OpenGL context. This can be achieved
95 by passing a pointer to a QRhiGles2NativeHandles to QRhi::create(). The
96 \l{QRhiGles2NativeHandles::context}{context} must be set to a non-null
97 value.
98
99 An alternative approach is to create a QOpenGLContext that
100 \l{QOpenGLContext::setShareContext()}{shares resources} with the other
101 engine's context and passing in that context via QRhiGles2NativeHandles.
102
103 The QRhi does not take ownership of the QOpenGLContext passed in via
104 QRhiGles2NativeHandles.
105 */
106

454/*!
455 Constructs a new QRhiGles2InitParams.
456
457 \l format is set to QSurfaceFormat::defaultFormat().
458 */
459QRhiGles2InitParams::QRhiGles2InitParams()
460{
461 format = QSurfaceFormat::defaultFormat();
462}
463
464/*!
465 \return a new QOffscreenSurface that can be used with a QRhi by passing it
466 via a QRhiGles2InitParams.
467
468 When \a format is not specified, its default value is the global default
469 format settable via QSurfaceFormat::setDefaultFormat().
470
471 \a format is adjusted as appropriate in order to avoid having problems
472 afterwards due to an incompatible context and surface.
473
474 \note This function must only be called on the gui/main thread.
475
476 \note It is the application's responsibility to destroy the returned
477 QOffscreenSurface on the gui/main thread once the associated QRhi has been
478 destroyed. The QRhi will not destroy the QOffscreenSurface.
479 */
480QOffscreenSurface *QRhiGles2InitParams::newFallbackSurface(const QSurfaceFormat &format)
481{
482 QSurfaceFormat fmt = format;
483
484 // To resolve all fields in the format as much as possible, create a context.
485 // This may be heavy, but allows avoiding BAD_MATCH on some systems.
486 QOpenGLContext tempContext;
487 tempContext.setFormat(fmt);
488 if (tempContext.create())
489 fmt = tempContext.format();
490 else
491 qWarning(msg: "QRhiGles2: Failed to create temporary context");
492
493 QOffscreenSurface *s = new QOffscreenSurface;
494 s->setFormat(fmt);
495 s->create();
496
497 return s;
498}
499
500QRhiGles2::QRhiGles2(QRhiGles2InitParams *params, QRhiGles2NativeHandles *importDevice)
501 : ofr(this)
502{
503 requestedFormat = params->format;
504 fallbackSurface = params->fallbackSurface;
505 maybeWindow = params->window; // may be null
506 maybeShareContext = params->shareContext; // may be null
507
508 importedContext = importDevice != nullptr;
509 if (importedContext) {
510 ctx = importDevice->context;
511 if (!ctx) {
512 qWarning(msg: "No OpenGL context given, cannot import");
513 importedContext = false;
514 }
515 }
516}
517
518static inline QSurface *currentSurfaceForCurrentContext(QOpenGLContext *ctx)
519{
520 if (QOpenGLContext::currentContext() != ctx)
521 return nullptr;
522
523 QSurface *currentSurface = ctx->surface();
524 if (!currentSurface)
525 return nullptr;
526
527 if (currentSurface->surfaceClass() == QSurface::Window && !currentSurface->surfaceHandle())
528 return nullptr;
529
530 return currentSurface;
531}
532
533QSurface *QRhiGles2::evaluateFallbackSurface() const
534{
535 // With Apple's deprecated OpenGL support we need to minimize the usage of
536 // QOffscreenSurface since delicate problems can pop up with
537 // NSOpenGLContext and drawables.
538#if defined(Q_OS_MACOS)
539 return maybeWindow && maybeWindow->handle() ? static_cast<QSurface *>(maybeWindow) : fallbackSurface;
540#else
541 return fallbackSurface;
542#endif
543}
544
545bool QRhiGles2::ensureContext(QSurface *surface) const
546{
547 if (!surface) {
548 // null means any surface is good because not going to render
549 if (currentSurfaceForCurrentContext(ctx))
550 return true;
551 // if the context is not already current with a valid surface, use our
552 // fallback surface, but platform specific quirks may apply
553 surface = evaluateFallbackSurface();
554 } else if (surface->surfaceClass() == QSurface::Window && !surface->surfaceHandle()) {
555 // the window is not usable anymore (no native window underneath), behave as if offscreen
556 surface = evaluateFallbackSurface();
557 } else if (!needsMakeCurrentDueToSwap && currentSurfaceForCurrentContext(ctx) == surface) {
558 // bail out if the makeCurrent is not necessary
559 return true;
560 }
561 needsMakeCurrentDueToSwap = false;
562
563 if (!ctx->makeCurrent(surface)) {
564 if (ctx->isValid()) {
565 qWarning(msg: "QRhiGles2: Failed to make context current. Expect bad things to happen.");
566 } else {
567 qWarning(msg: "QRhiGles2: Context is lost.");
568 contextLost = true;
569 }
570 return false;
571 }
572
573 return true;
574}

576static inline GLenum toGlCompressedTextureFormat(QRhiTexture::Format format, QRhiTexture::Flags flags)
577{
578 const bool srgb = flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::sRGB);
579 switch (format) {
580 case QRhiTexture::BC1:
581 return srgb ? 0x8C4C : 0x83F0;
582 case QRhiTexture::BC2:
583 return srgb ? 0x8C4E : 0x83F2;
584 case QRhiTexture::BC3:
585 return srgb ? 0x8C4F : 0x83F3;
586
587 case QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGB8:
588 return srgb ? 0x9275 : 0x9274;
589 case QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGB8A1:
590 return srgb ? 0x9277 : 0x9276;
591 case QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGBA8:
592 return srgb ? 0x9279 : 0x9278;
593
594 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_4x4:
595 return srgb ? 0x93D0 : 0x93B0;
596 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_5x4:
597 return srgb ? 0x93D1 : 0x93B1;
598 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_5x5:
599 return srgb ? 0x93D2 : 0x93B2;
600 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_6x5:
601 return srgb ? 0x93D3 : 0x93B3;
602 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_6x6:
603 return srgb ? 0x93D4 : 0x93B4;
604 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x5:
605 return srgb ? 0x93D5 : 0x93B5;
606 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x6:
607 return srgb ? 0x93D6 : 0x93B6;
608 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x8:
609 return srgb ? 0x93D7 : 0x93B7;
610 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x5:
611 return srgb ? 0x93D8 : 0x93B8;
612 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x6:
613 return srgb ? 0x93D9 : 0x93B9;
614 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x8:
615 return srgb ? 0x93DA : 0x93BA;
616 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x10:
617 return srgb ? 0x93DB : 0x93BB;
618 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_12x10:
619 return srgb ? 0x93DC : 0x93BC;
620 case QRhiTexture::ASTC_12x12:
621 return srgb ? 0x93DD : 0x93BD;
622
623 default:
624 return 0; // this is reachable, just return an invalid format
625 }
626}
627
628bool QRhiGles2::create(QRhi::Flags flags)
629{
630 Q_ASSERT(fallbackSurface);
631 rhiFlags = flags;
632
633 if (!importedContext) {
634 ctx = new QOpenGLContext;
635 ctx->setFormat(requestedFormat);
636 if (maybeShareContext) {
637 ctx->setShareContext(maybeShareContext);
638 ctx->setScreen(maybeShareContext->screen());
639 } else if (QOpenGLContext *shareContext = qt_gl_global_share_context()) {
640 ctx->setShareContext(shareContext);
641 ctx->setScreen(shareContext->screen());
642 } else if (maybeWindow) {
643 ctx->setScreen(maybeWindow->screen());
644 }
645 if (!ctx->create()) {
646 qWarning(msg: "QRhiGles2: Failed to create context");
647 delete ctx;
648 ctx = nullptr;
649 return false;
650 }
651 qCDebug(QRHI_LOG_INFO) << "Created OpenGL context" << ctx->format();
652 }
653
654 if (!ensureContext(surface: maybeWindow ? maybeWindow : fallbackSurface)) // see 'window' discussion in QRhiGles2InitParams comments
655 return false;
656
657 f = static_cast<QOpenGLExtensions *>(ctx->extraFunctions());
658
659 if (!caps.gles) {
660 glPolygonMode = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(GLenum, GLenum)>(
661 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glPolygonMode")));
662
663 glTexImage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(
664 GLenum, GLint, GLint, GLsizei, GLint, GLenum, GLenum, const void *)>(
665 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glTexImage1D")));
666
667 glTexStorage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(GLenum, GLint, GLenum, GLsizei)>(
668 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glTexStorage1D")));
669
670 glTexSubImage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(
671 GLenum, GLint, GLint, GLsizei, GLenum, GLenum, const GLvoid *)>(
672 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glTexSubImage1D")));
673
674 glCopyTexSubImage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(GLenum, GLint, GLint, GLint,
675 GLint, GLsizei)>(
676 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glCopyTexSubImage1D")));
677
678 glCompressedTexImage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(
679 GLenum, GLint, GLenum, GLsizei, GLint, GLsizei, const GLvoid *)>(
680 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glCompressedTexImage1D")));
681
682 glCompressedTexSubImage1D = reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(
683 GLenum, GLint, GLint, GLsizei, GLenum, GLsizei, const GLvoid *)>(
684 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glCompressedTexSubImage1D")));
685
686 glFramebufferTexture1D =
687 reinterpret_cast<void(QOPENGLF_APIENTRYP)(GLenum, GLenum, GLenum, GLuint, GLint)>(
688 ctx->getProcAddress(QByteArrayLiteral("glFramebufferTexture1D")));
689 }
690
691 const char *vendor = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(f->glGetString(GL_VENDOR));
692 const char *renderer = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(f->glGetString(GL_RENDERER));
693 const char *version = reinterpret_cast<const char *>(f->glGetString(GL_VERSION));
694 if (vendor && renderer && version)
695 qCDebug(QRHI_LOG_INFO, "OpenGL VENDOR: %s RENDERER: %s VERSION: %s", vendor, renderer, version);
696
697 if (vendor) {
698 driverInfoStruct.deviceName += QByteArray(vendor);
699 driverInfoStruct.deviceName += ' ';
700 }
701 if (renderer) {
702 driverInfoStruct.deviceName += QByteArray(renderer);
703 driverInfoStruct.deviceName += ' ';
704 }
705 if (version)
706 driverInfoStruct.deviceName += QByteArray(version);
707
708 const QSurfaceFormat actualFormat = ctx->format();
709
710 caps.ctxMajor = actualFormat.majorVersion();
711 caps.ctxMinor = actualFormat.minorVersion();
712
713 GLint n = 0;
714 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_NUM_COMPRESSED_TEXTURE_FORMATS, params: &n);
715 if (n > 0) {
716 QVarLengthArray<GLint, 16> compressedTextureFormats(n);
717 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_COMPRESSED_TEXTURE_FORMATS, params: compressedTextureFormats.data());
718 for (GLint format : compressedTextureFormats)
719 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: format);
720
721 }
722 // The above looks nice, if only it worked always. With GLES the list we
723 // query is likely the full list of compressed formats (mostly anything
724 // that can be decoded). With OpenGL however the list is not required to
725 // include all formats due to the way the spec is worded. For instance, we
726 // cannot rely on ASTC formats being present in the list on non-ES. Some
727 // drivers do include them (Intel, NVIDIA), some don't (Mesa). On the other
728 // hand, relying on extension strings only is not ok: for example, Intel
729 // reports GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_ldr whereas NVIDIA doesn't. So
730 // the only reasonable thing to do is to query the list always and then see
731 // if there is something we can add - if not already in there.
732 std::array<QRhiTexture::Flags, 2> textureVariantFlags;
733 textureVariantFlags[0] = {};
734 textureVariantFlags[1] = QRhiTexture::sRGB;
735 if (f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::DDSTextureCompression)) {
736 for (QRhiTexture::Flags f : textureVariantFlags) {
737 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::BC1, flags: f));
738 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::BC2, flags: f));
739 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::BC3, flags: f));
740 }
741 }
742 if (f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::ETC2TextureCompression)) {
743 for (QRhiTexture::Flags f : textureVariantFlags) {
744 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGB8, flags: f));
745 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGB8A1, flags: f));
746 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ETC2_RGBA8, flags: f));
747 }
748 }
749 if (f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::ASTCTextureCompression)) {
750 for (QRhiTexture::Flags f : textureVariantFlags) {
751 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_4x4, flags: f));
752 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_5x4, flags: f));
753 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_5x5, flags: f));
754 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_6x5, flags: f));
755 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_6x6, flags: f));
756 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x5, flags: f));
757 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x6, flags: f));
758 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_8x8, flags: f));
759 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x5, flags: f));
760 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x8, flags: f));
761 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_10x10, flags: f));
762 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_12x10, flags: f));
763 supportedCompressedFormats.insert(value: toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: QRhiTexture::ASTC_12x12, flags: f));
764 }
765 }
766
767 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE, params: &caps.maxTextureSize);
768
769 caps.gles = actualFormat.renderableType() == QSurfaceFormat::OpenGLES;
770
771 if (!caps.gles || caps.ctxMajor >= 3) {
772 // non-ES or ES 3.0+
773 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS, params: &caps.maxDrawBuffers);
774 caps.hasDrawBuffersFunc = true;
775 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_SAMPLES, params: &caps.maxSamples);
776 caps.maxSamples = qMax(a: 1, b: caps.maxSamples);
777 } else {
778 // ES 2.0 / WebGL 1
779 caps.maxDrawBuffers = 1;
780 caps.hasDrawBuffersFunc = false;
781 // This does not mean MSAA is not supported, just that we cannot query
782 // the supported sample counts.
783 caps.maxSamples = 1;
784 }
785
786 caps.msaaRenderBuffer = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::FramebufferMultisample)
787 && f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::FramebufferBlit);
788
789 caps.npotTextureFull = f->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::NPOTTextures)
790 && f->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::NPOTTextureRepeat);
791
792 if (caps.gles)
793 caps.fixedIndexPrimitiveRestart = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
794 else
795 caps.fixedIndexPrimitiveRestart = caps.ctxMajor > 4 || (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor >= 3); // 4.3
796
797 if (caps.fixedIndexPrimitiveRestart) {
798#ifdef Q_OS_WASM
799 // WebGL 2 behaves as if GL_PRIMITIVE_RESTART_FIXED_INDEX was always
800 // enabled (i.e. matching D3D/Metal), and the value cannot be passed to
801 // glEnable, so skip the call.
802#else
803 f->glEnable(GL_PRIMITIVE_RESTART_FIXED_INDEX);
804#endif
805 }
806
807 caps.bgraExternalFormat = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::BGRATextureFormat);
808 caps.bgraInternalFormat = caps.bgraExternalFormat && caps.gles;
809 caps.r8Format = f->hasOpenGLFeature(feature: QOpenGLFunctions::TextureRGFormats);
810 caps.r16Format = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::Sized16Formats);
811 caps.floatFormats = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0 or ES 3.0
812 caps.rgb10Formats = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0 or ES 3.0
813 caps.depthTexture = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0 or ES 3.0
814 caps.packedDepthStencil = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::PackedDepthStencil);
815#ifdef Q_OS_WASM
816 caps.needsDepthStencilCombinedAttach = true;
817#else
818 caps.needsDepthStencilCombinedAttach = false;
819#endif
820 caps.srgbCapableDefaultFramebuffer = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::SRGBFrameBuffer);
821 caps.coreProfile = actualFormat.profile() == QSurfaceFormat::CoreProfile;
822
823 if (caps.gles)
824 caps.uniformBuffers = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
825 else
826 caps.uniformBuffers = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 1); // 3.1
827
828 caps.elementIndexUint = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::ElementIndexUint);
829 caps.depth24 = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::Depth24);
830 caps.rgba8Format = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::Sized8Formats);
831
832 if (caps.gles)
833 caps.instancing = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
834 else
835 caps.instancing = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 3); // 3.3
836
837 caps.baseVertex = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2); // 3.2 or ES 3.2
838
839 if (caps.gles)
840 caps.compute = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 1); // ES 3.1
841 else
842 caps.compute = caps.ctxMajor > 4 || (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor >= 3); // 4.3
843
844 if (caps.compute) {
845 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_INVOCATIONS, params: &caps.maxThreadsPerThreadGroup);
846 GLint tgPerDim[3];
847 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_COUNT, index: 0, data: &tgPerDim[0]);
848 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_COUNT, index: 1, data: &tgPerDim[1]);
849 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_COUNT, index: 2, data: &tgPerDim[2]);
850 caps.maxThreadGroupsPerDimension = qMin(a: tgPerDim[0], b: qMin(a: tgPerDim[1], b: tgPerDim[2]));
851 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, index: 0, data: &caps.maxThreadGroupsX);
852 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, index: 1, data: &caps.maxThreadGroupsY);
853 f->glGetIntegeri_v(GL_MAX_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, index: 2, data: &caps.maxThreadGroupsZ);
854 }
855
856 if (caps.gles)
857 caps.textureCompareMode = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
858 else
859 caps.textureCompareMode = true;
860
861 // proper as in ES 3.0 (glMapBufferRange), not the old glMapBuffer
862 // extension(s) (which is not in ES 3.0...messy)
863 caps.properMapBuffer = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::MapBufferRange);
864
865 if (caps.gles)
866 caps.nonBaseLevelFramebufferTexture = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
867 else
868 caps.nonBaseLevelFramebufferTexture = true;
869
870 caps.texelFetch = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0 or ES 3.0
871 caps.intAttributes = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0 or ES 3.0
872 caps.screenSpaceDerivatives = f->hasOpenGLExtension(extension: QOpenGLExtensions::StandardDerivatives);
873
874 if (caps.gles)
875 caps.multisampledTexture = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 1); // ES 3.1
876 else
877 caps.multisampledTexture = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0
878
879 // Program binary support: only the core stuff, do not bother with the old
880 // extensions like GL_OES_get_program_binary
881 if (caps.gles)
882 caps.programBinary = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // ES 3.0
883 else
884 caps.programBinary = caps.ctxMajor > 4 || (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor >= 1); // 4.1
885
886 if (caps.programBinary) {
887 GLint fmtCount = 0;
888 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_NUM_PROGRAM_BINARY_FORMATS, params: &fmtCount);
889 if (fmtCount < 1)
890 caps.programBinary = false;
891 }
892
893 caps.texture3D = caps.ctxMajor >= 3; // 3.0
894
895 if (caps.gles)
896 caps.texture1D = false; // ES
897 else
898 caps.texture1D = glTexImage1D && (caps.ctxMajor >= 2); // 2.0
899
900 if (caps.gles)
901 caps.tessellation = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2); // ES 3.2
902 else
903 caps.tessellation = caps.ctxMajor >= 4; // 4.0
904
905 if (caps.gles)
906 caps.geometryShader = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2); // ES 3.2
907 else
908 caps.geometryShader = caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2); // 3.2
909
910 if (caps.ctxMajor >= 3) { // 3.0 or ES 3.0
911 GLint maxArraySize = 0;
912 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_ARRAY_TEXTURE_LAYERS, params: &maxArraySize);
913 caps.maxTextureArraySize = maxArraySize;
914 } else {
915 caps.maxTextureArraySize = 0;
916 }
917
918 // The ES 2.0 spec only has MAX_xxxx_VECTORS. ES 3.0 and up has both
919 // *VECTORS and *COMPONENTS. OpenGL 2.0-4.0 only has MAX_xxxx_COMPONENTS.
920 // 4.1 and above has both. What a mess.
921 if (caps.gles) {
922 GLint maxVertexUniformVectors = 0;
923 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_VECTORS, params: &maxVertexUniformVectors);
924 GLint maxFragmentUniformVectors = 0;
925 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_VECTORS, params: &maxFragmentUniformVectors);
926 caps.maxUniformVectors = qMin(a: maxVertexUniformVectors, b: maxFragmentUniformVectors);
927 } else {
928 GLint maxVertexUniformComponents = 0;
929 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS, params: &maxVertexUniformComponents);
930 GLint maxFragmentUniformComponents = 0;
931 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS, params: &maxFragmentUniformComponents);
932 caps.maxUniformVectors = qMin(a: maxVertexUniformComponents, b: maxFragmentUniformComponents) / 4;
933 }
934
935 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS, params: &caps.maxVertexInputs);
936
937 if (caps.gles) {
938 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VARYING_VECTORS, params: &caps.maxVertexOutputs);
939 } else if (caps.ctxMajor >= 3) {
940 GLint components = 0;
941 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VARYING_COMPONENTS, params: &components);
942 caps.maxVertexOutputs = components / 4;
943 } else {
944 // OpenGL before 3.0 only has this, and not the same as
945 // MAX_VARYING_COMPONENTS strictly speaking, but will do.
946 GLint components = 0;
947 f->glGetIntegerv(GL_MAX_VARYING_FLOATS, params: &components);
948 if (components > 0)
949 caps.maxVertexOutputs = components / 4;
950 }
951
952 if (!caps.gles) {
953 f->glEnable(GL_VERTEX_PROGRAM_POINT_SIZE);
954 f->glEnable(GL_POINT_SPRITE);
955 } // else (with gles) these are always on
956
957 // Match D3D and others when it comes to seamless cubemap filtering.
958 // ES 3.0+ has this always enabled. (hopefully)
959 // ES 2.0 and GL < 3.2 will not have it.
960 if (!caps.gles && (caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2)))
961 f->glEnable(GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_SEAMLESS);
962
963 nativeHandlesStruct.context = ctx;
964
965 contextLost = false;
966
967 return true;
968}
969
970void QRhiGles2::destroy()
971{
972 if (!f)
973 return;
974
975 ensureContext();
976 executeDeferredReleases();
977
978 if (vao) {
979 f->glDeleteVertexArrays(n: 1, arrays: &vao);
980 vao = 0;
981 }
982
983 for (uint shader : m_shaderCache)
984 f->glDeleteShader(shader);
985 m_shaderCache.clear();
986
987 if (!importedContext) {
988 delete ctx;
989 ctx = nullptr;
990 }
991
992 f = nullptr;
993}
994
995void QRhiGles2::executeDeferredReleases()
996{
997 for (int i = releaseQueue.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
998 const QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry &e(releaseQueue[i]);
999 switch (e.type) {
1000 case QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry::Buffer:
1001 f->glDeleteBuffers(n: 1, buffers: &e.buffer.buffer);
1002 break;
1003 case QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry::Pipeline:
1004 f->glDeleteProgram(program: e.pipeline.program);
1005 break;
1006 case QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry::Texture:
1007 f->glDeleteTextures(n: 1, textures: &e.texture.texture);
1008 break;
1009 case QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry::RenderBuffer:
1010 f->glDeleteRenderbuffers(n: 1, renderbuffers: &e.renderbuffer.renderbuffer);
1011 f->glDeleteRenderbuffers(n: 1, renderbuffers: &e.renderbuffer.renderbuffer2);
1012 break;
1013 case QRhiGles2::DeferredReleaseEntry::TextureRenderTarget:
1014 f->glDeleteFramebuffers(n: 1, framebuffers: &e.textureRenderTarget.framebuffer);
1015 break;
1016 default:
1017 Q_UNREACHABLE();
1018 break;
1019 }
1020 releaseQueue.removeAt(i);
1021 }
1022}

1024QList<int> QRhiGles2::supportedSampleCounts() const
1025{
1026 if (supportedSampleCountList.isEmpty()) {
1027 // 1, 2, 4, 8, ...
1028 for (int i = 1; i <= caps.maxSamples; i *= 2)
1029 supportedSampleCountList.append(t: i);
1030 }
1031 return supportedSampleCountList;
1032}
1033
1034int QRhiGles2::effectiveSampleCount(int sampleCount) const
1035{
1036 // Stay compatible with QSurfaceFormat and friends where samples == 0 means the same as 1.
1037 const int s = qBound(min: 1, val: sampleCount, max: 64);
1038 if (!supportedSampleCounts().contains(t: s)) {
1039 qWarning(msg: "Attempted to set unsupported sample count %d", sampleCount);
1040 return 1;
1041 }
1042 return s;
1043}

1082static inline void toGlTextureFormat(QRhiTexture::Format format, const QRhiGles2::Caps &caps,
1083 GLenum *glintformat, GLenum *glsizedintformat,
1084 GLenum *glformat, GLenum *gltype)
1085{
1086 switch (format) {
1087 case QRhiTexture::RGBA8:
1088 *glintformat = GL_RGBA;
1089 *glsizedintformat = caps.rgba8Format ? GL_RGBA8 : GL_RGBA;
1090 *glformat = GL_RGBA;
1091 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1092 break;
1093 case QRhiTexture::BGRA8:
1094 *glintformat = caps.bgraInternalFormat ? GL_BGRA : GL_RGBA;
1095 *glsizedintformat = caps.rgba8Format ? GL_RGBA8 : GL_RGBA;
1096 *glformat = GL_BGRA;
1097 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1098 break;
1099 case QRhiTexture::R16:
1100 *glintformat = GL_R16;
1101 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1102 *glformat = GL_RED;
1103 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1104 break;
1105 case QRhiTexture::RG16:
1106 *glintformat = GL_RG16;
1107 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1108 *glformat = GL_RG;
1109 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1110 break;
1111 case QRhiTexture::R8:
1112 *glintformat = GL_R8;
1113 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1114 *glformat = GL_RED;
1115 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1116 break;
1117 case QRhiTexture::RG8:
1118 *glintformat = GL_RG8;
1119 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1120 *glformat = GL_RG;
1121 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1122 break;
1123 case QRhiTexture::RED_OR_ALPHA8:
1124 *glintformat = caps.coreProfile ? GL_R8 : GL_ALPHA;
1125 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1126 *glformat = caps.coreProfile ? GL_RED : GL_ALPHA;
1127 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1128 break;
1129 case QRhiTexture::RGBA16F:
1130 *glintformat = GL_RGBA16F;
1131 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1132 *glformat = GL_RGBA;
1133 *gltype = GL_HALF_FLOAT;
1134 break;
1135 case QRhiTexture::RGBA32F:
1136 *glintformat = GL_RGBA32F;
1137 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1138 *glformat = GL_RGBA;
1139 *gltype = GL_FLOAT;
1140 break;
1141 case QRhiTexture::R16F:
1142 *glintformat = GL_R16F;
1143 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1144 *glformat = GL_RED;
1145 *gltype = GL_HALF_FLOAT;
1146 break;
1147 case QRhiTexture::R32F:
1148 *glintformat = GL_R32F;
1149 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1150 *glformat = GL_RED;
1151 *gltype = GL_FLOAT;
1152 break;
1153 case QRhiTexture::RGB10A2:
1154 *glintformat = GL_RGB10_A2;
1155 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1156 *glformat = GL_RGBA;
1157 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV;
1158 break;
1159 case QRhiTexture::D16:
1160 *glintformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT16;
1161 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1162 *glformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT;
1163 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1164 break;
1165 case QRhiTexture::D24:
1166 *glintformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24;
1167 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1168 *glformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT;
1169 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1170 break;
1171 case QRhiTexture::D24S8:
1172 *glintformat = GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8;
1173 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1174 *glformat = GL_DEPTH_STENCIL;
1175 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
1176 break;
1177 case QRhiTexture::D32F:
1178 *glintformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT32F;
1179 *glsizedintformat = *glintformat;
1180 *glformat = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT;
1181 *gltype = GL_FLOAT;
1182 break;
1183 default:
1184 Q_UNREACHABLE();
1185 *glintformat = GL_RGBA;
1186 *glsizedintformat = caps.rgba8Format ? GL_RGBA8 : GL_RGBA;
1187 *glformat = GL_RGBA;
1188 *gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
1189 break;
1190 }
1191}

1193bool QRhiGles2::isTextureFormatSupported(QRhiTexture::Format format, QRhiTexture::Flags flags) const
1194{
1195 if (isCompressedFormat(format))
1196 return supportedCompressedFormats.contains(value: GLint(toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format, flags)));
1197
1198 switch (format) {
1199 case QRhiTexture::D16:
1200 case QRhiTexture::D32F:
1201 return caps.depthTexture;
1202
1203 case QRhiTexture::D24:
1204 return caps.depth24;
1205
1206 case QRhiTexture::D24S8:
1207 return caps.depth24 && caps.packedDepthStencil;
1208
1209 case QRhiTexture::BGRA8:
1210 return caps.bgraExternalFormat;
1211
1212 case QRhiTexture::R8:
1213 return caps.r8Format;
1214
1215 case QRhiTexture::RG8:
1216 return caps.r8Format;
1217
1218 case QRhiTexture::R16:
1219 return caps.r16Format;
1220
1221 case QRhiTexture::RG16:
1222 return caps.r16Format;
1223
1224 case QRhiTexture::RGBA16F:
1225 case QRhiTexture::RGBA32F:
1226 return caps.floatFormats;
1227
1228 case QRhiTexture::R16F:
1229 case QRhiTexture::R32F:
1230 return caps.floatFormats;
1231
1232 case QRhiTexture::RGB10A2:
1233 return caps.rgb10Formats;
1234
1235 default:
1236 break;
1237 }
1238
1239 return true;
1240}
1241
1242bool QRhiGles2::isFeatureSupported(QRhi::Feature feature) const
1243{
1244 switch (feature) {
1245 case QRhi::MultisampleTexture:

1299 case QRhi::RenderBufferImport:
1300 return true;
1301 case QRhi::ThreeDimensionalTextures:

1404
1405struct QGles2PipelineCacheDataHeader
1406{
1407 quint32 rhiId;
1408 quint32 arch;
1409 quint32 programBinaryCount;
1410 quint32 dataSize;
1411 char driver[240];
1412};
1413
1414QByteArray QRhiGles2::pipelineCacheData()
1415{
1416 Q_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(QGles2PipelineCacheDataHeader) == 256);
1417
1418 if (m_pipelineCache.isEmpty())
1419 return QByteArray();
1420
1421 QGles2PipelineCacheDataHeader header;
1422 memset(s: &header, c: 0, n: sizeof(header));
1423 header.rhiId = pipelineCacheRhiId();
1424 header.arch = quint32(sizeof(void*));
1425 header.programBinaryCount = m_pipelineCache.size();
1426 const size_t driverStrLen = qMin(a: sizeof(header.driver) - 1, b: size_t(driverInfoStruct.deviceName.size()));
1427 if (driverStrLen)
1428 memcpy(dest: header.driver, src: driverInfoStruct.deviceName.constData(), n: driverStrLen);
1429 header.driver[driverStrLen] = '\0';
1430
1431 const size_t dataOffset = sizeof(header);
1432 size_t dataSize = 0;
1433 for (auto it = m_pipelineCache.cbegin(), end = m_pipelineCache.cend(); it != end; ++it) {
1434 dataSize += sizeof(quint32) + it.key().size()
1435 + sizeof(quint32) + it->data.size()
1436 + sizeof(quint32);
1437 }
1438
1439 QByteArray buf(dataOffset + dataSize, Qt::Uninitialized);
1440 char *p = buf.data() + dataOffset;
1441 for (auto it = m_pipelineCache.cbegin(), end = m_pipelineCache.cend(); it != end; ++it) {
1442 const QByteArray key = it.key();
1443 const QByteArray data = it->data;
1444 const quint32 format = it->format;
1445
1446 quint32 i = key.size();
1447 memcpy(dest: p, src: &i, n: 4);
1448 p += 4;
1449 memcpy(dest: p, src: key.constData(), n: key.size());
1450 p += key.size();
1451
1452 i = data.size();
1453 memcpy(dest: p, src: &i, n: 4);
1454 p += 4;
1455 memcpy(dest: p, src: data.constData(), n: data.size());
1456 p += data.size();
1457
1458 memcpy(dest: p, src: &format, n: 4);
1459 p += 4;
1460 }
1461 Q_ASSERT(p == buf.data() + dataOffset + dataSize);
1462
1463 header.dataSize = quint32(dataSize);
1464 memcpy(dest: buf.data(), src: &header, n: sizeof(header));
1465
1466 return buf;
1467}
1468
1469void QRhiGles2::setPipelineCacheData(const QByteArray &data)
1470{
1471 if (data.isEmpty())
1472 return;
1473
1474 const size_t headerSize = sizeof(QGles2PipelineCacheDataHeader);
1475 if (data.size() < qsizetype(headerSize)) {
1476 qWarning(msg: "setPipelineCacheData: Invalid blob size (header incomplete)");
1477 return;
1478 }
1479 const size_t dataOffset = headerSize;
1480 QGles2PipelineCacheDataHeader header;
1481 memcpy(dest: &header, src: data.constData(), n: headerSize);
1482
1483 const quint32 rhiId = pipelineCacheRhiId();
1484 if (header.rhiId != rhiId) {
1485 qWarning(msg: "setPipelineCacheData: The data is for a different QRhi version or backend (%u, %u)",
1486 rhiId, header.rhiId);
1487 return;
1488 }
1489 const quint32 arch = quint32(sizeof(void*));
1490 if (header.arch != arch) {
1491 qWarning(msg: "setPipelineCacheData: Architecture does not match (%u, %u)",
1492 arch, header.arch);
1493 return;
1494 }
1495 if (header.programBinaryCount == 0)
1496 return;
1497
1498 const size_t driverStrLen = qMin(a: sizeof(header.driver) - 1, b: size_t(driverInfoStruct.deviceName.size()));
1499 if (strncmp(s1: header.driver, s2: driverInfoStruct.deviceName.constData(), n: driverStrLen)) {
1500 qWarning(msg: "setPipelineCacheData: OpenGL vendor/renderer/version does not match");
1501 return;
1502 }
1503
1504 if (data.size() < qsizetype(dataOffset + header.dataSize)) {
1505 qWarning(msg: "setPipelineCacheData: Invalid blob size (data incomplete)");
1506 return;
1507 }
1508
1509 m_pipelineCache.clear();
1510
1511 const char *p = data.constData() + dataOffset;
1512 for (quint32 i = 0; i < header.programBinaryCount; ++i) {
1513 quint32 len = 0;
1514 memcpy(dest: &len, src: p, n: 4);
1515 p += 4;
1516 QByteArray key(len, Qt::Uninitialized);
1517 memcpy(dest: key.data(), src: p, n: len);
1518 p += len;
1519
1520 memcpy(dest: &len, src: p, n: 4);
1521 p += 4;
1522 QByteArray data(len, Qt::Uninitialized);
1523 memcpy(dest: data.data(), src: p, n: len);
1524 p += len;
1525
1526 quint32 format;
1527 memcpy(dest: &format, src: p, n: 4);
1528 p += 4;
1529
1530 m_pipelineCache.insert(key, value: { .format: format, .data: data });
1531 }
1532
1533 qCDebug(QRHI_LOG_INFO, "Seeded pipeline cache with %d program binaries", int(m_pipelineCache.size()));
1534}

1578void QRhiGles2::setGraphicsPipeline(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, QRhiGraphicsPipeline *ps)
1579{

1581 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::RenderPass);
1582 QGles2GraphicsPipeline *psD = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, ps);
1583 const bool pipelineChanged = cbD->currentGraphicsPipeline != ps || cbD->currentPipelineGeneration != psD->generation;
1584
1585 if (pipelineChanged) {
1586 cbD->currentGraphicsPipeline = ps;
1587 cbD->currentComputePipeline = nullptr;
1588 cbD->currentPipelineGeneration = psD->generation;

1591 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindGraphicsPipeline;
1592 cmd.args.bindGraphicsPipeline.ps = ps;
1593 }

1595
1596void QRhiGles2::setShaderResources(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, QRhiShaderResourceBindings *srb,
1597 int dynamicOffsetCount,
1598 const QRhiCommandBuffer::DynamicOffset *dynamicOffsets)
1599{
1600 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
1601 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass != QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass);
1602 QGles2GraphicsPipeline *gfxPsD = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, cbD->currentGraphicsPipeline);
1603 QGles2ComputePipeline *compPsD = QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, cbD->currentComputePipeline);
1604
1605 if (!srb) {
1606 if (gfxPsD)
1607 srb = gfxPsD->m_shaderResourceBindings;
1608 else
1609 srb = compPsD->m_shaderResourceBindings;
1610 }
1611
1612 QGles2ShaderResourceBindings *srbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2ShaderResourceBindings, srb);
1613 if (cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
1614 QRhiPassResourceTracker &passResTracker(cbD->passResTrackers[cbD->currentPassResTrackerIndex]);
1615 for (int i = 0, ie = srbD->m_bindings.size(); i != ie; ++i) {
1616 const QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Data *b = srbD->m_bindings.at(idx: i).data();
1617 switch (b->type) {
1618 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::UniformBuffer:
1619 // no BufUniformRead / AccessUniform because no real uniform buffers are used
1620 break;
1621 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::SampledTexture:
1622 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Texture:
1623 for (int elem = 0; elem < b->u.stex.count; ++elem) {
1624 trackedRegisterTexture(passResTracker: &passResTracker,
1625 QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, b->u.stex.texSamplers[elem].tex),
1626 access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexSample,
1627 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::toPassTrackerTextureStage(stages: b->stage));
1628 }
1629 break;
1630 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad:
1631 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore:
1632 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoadStore:
1633 {
1634 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, b->u.simage.tex);
1635 QRhiPassResourceTracker::TextureAccess access;
1636 if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad)
1637 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexStorageLoad;
1638 else if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore)
1639 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexStorageStore;
1640 else
1641 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexStorageLoadStore;
1642 trackedRegisterTexture(passResTracker: &passResTracker, texD, access,
1643 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::toPassTrackerTextureStage(stages: b->stage));
1644 }
1645 break;
1646 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoad:
1647 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferStore:
1648 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoadStore:
1649 {
1650 QGles2Buffer *bufD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Buffer, b->u.sbuf.buf);
1651 QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufferAccess access;
1652 if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoad)
1653 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufStorageLoad;
1654 else if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferStore)
1655 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufStorageStore;
1656 else
1657 access = QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufStorageLoadStore;
1658 trackedRegisterBuffer(passResTracker: &passResTracker, bufD, access,
1659 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::toPassTrackerBufferStage(stages: b->stage));
1660 }
1661 break;
1662 default:
1663 break;
1664 }
1665 }
1666 }
1667
1668 bool srbChanged = gfxPsD ? (cbD->currentGraphicsSrb != srb) : (cbD->currentComputeSrb != srb);
1669
1670 // The Command::BindShaderResources command generated below is what will
1671 // cause uniforms to be set (glUniformNxx). This needs some special
1672 // handling here in this backend without real uniform buffers, because,
1673 // like in other backends, we optimize out the setShaderResources when the
1674 // srb that was set before is attempted to be set again on the command
1675 // buffer, but that is incorrect if the same srb is now used with another
1676 // pipeline. (because that could mean a glUseProgram not followed by
1677 // up-to-date glUniform calls, i.e. with GL we have a strong dependency
1678 // between the pipeline (== program) and the srb, unlike other APIs) This
1679 // is the reason there is a second level of srb(+generation) tracking in
1680 // the pipeline objects.
1681 if (gfxPsD && (gfxPsD->currentSrb != srb || gfxPsD->currentSrbGeneration != srbD->generation)) {
1682 srbChanged = true;
1683 gfxPsD->currentSrb = srb;
1684 gfxPsD->currentSrbGeneration = srbD->generation;
1685 } else if (compPsD && (compPsD->currentSrb != srb || compPsD->currentSrbGeneration != srbD->generation)) {
1686 srbChanged = true;
1687 compPsD->currentSrb = srb;
1688 compPsD->currentSrbGeneration = srbD->generation;
1689 }
1690
1691 if (srbChanged || cbD->currentSrbGeneration != srbD->generation || srbD->hasDynamicOffset) {
1692 if (gfxPsD) {
1693 cbD->currentGraphicsSrb = srb;
1694 cbD->currentComputeSrb = nullptr;
1695 } else {
1696 cbD->currentGraphicsSrb = nullptr;
1697 cbD->currentComputeSrb = srb;
1698 }
1699 cbD->currentSrbGeneration = srbD->generation;
1700
1701 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
1702 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindShaderResources;
1703 cmd.args.bindShaderResources.maybeGraphicsPs = gfxPsD;
1704 cmd.args.bindShaderResources.maybeComputePs = compPsD;
1705 cmd.args.bindShaderResources.srb = srb;
1706 cmd.args.bindShaderResources.dynamicOffsetCount = 0;
1707 if (srbD->hasDynamicOffset) {
1708 if (dynamicOffsetCount < QGles2CommandBuffer::MAX_DYNAMIC_OFFSET_COUNT) {
1709 cmd.args.bindShaderResources.dynamicOffsetCount = dynamicOffsetCount;
1710 uint *p = cmd.args.bindShaderResources.dynamicOffsetPairs;
1711 for (int i = 0; i < dynamicOffsetCount; ++i) {
1712 const QRhiCommandBuffer::DynamicOffset &dynOfs(dynamicOffsets[i]);
1713 *p++ = uint(dynOfs.first);
1714 *p++ = dynOfs.second;
1715 }
1716 } else {
1717 qWarning(msg: "Too many dynamic offsets (%d, max is %d)",
1718 dynamicOffsetCount, QGles2CommandBuffer::MAX_DYNAMIC_OFFSET_COUNT);
1719 }
1720 }
1721 }
1722}
1723
1724void QRhiGles2::setVertexInput(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb,
1725 int startBinding, int bindingCount, const QRhiCommandBuffer::VertexInput *bindings,
1726 QRhiBuffer *indexBuf, quint32 indexOffset, QRhiCommandBuffer::IndexFormat indexFormat)
1727{
1728 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
1729 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::RenderPass);
1730 QRhiPassResourceTracker &passResTracker(cbD->passResTrackers[cbD->currentPassResTrackerIndex]);
1731
1732 for (int i = 0; i < bindingCount; ++i) {
1733 QRhiBuffer *buf = bindings[i].first;
1734 quint32 ofs = bindings[i].second;
1735 QGles2Buffer *bufD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Buffer, buf);
1736 Q_ASSERT(bufD->m_usage.testFlag(QRhiBuffer::VertexBuffer));
1737
1738 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
1739 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindVertexBuffer;
1740 cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.ps = cbD->currentGraphicsPipeline;
1741 cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.buffer = bufD->buffer;
1742 cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.offset = ofs;
1743 cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.binding = startBinding + i;
1744
1745 if (cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
1746 trackedRegisterBuffer(passResTracker: &passResTracker, bufD, access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufVertexInput,
1747 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufVertexInputStage);
1748 }
1749 }
1750
1751 if (indexBuf) {
1752 QGles2Buffer *ibufD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Buffer, indexBuf);
1753 Q_ASSERT(ibufD->m_usage.testFlag(QRhiBuffer::IndexBuffer));
1754
1755 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
1756 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindIndexBuffer;
1757 cmd.args.bindIndexBuffer.buffer = ibufD->buffer;
1758 cmd.args.bindIndexBuffer.offset = indexOffset;
1759 cmd.args.bindIndexBuffer.type = indexFormat == QRhiCommandBuffer::IndexUInt16 ? GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT : GL_UNSIGNED_INT;
1760
1761 if (cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
1762 trackedRegisterBuffer(passResTracker: &passResTracker, bufD: ibufD, access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufIndexRead,
1763 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::BufVertexInputStage);
1764 }
1765 }
1766}

1768void QRhiGles2::setViewport(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, const QRhiViewport &viewport)
1769{
1770 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
1771 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::RenderPass);
1772
1773 const std::array<float, 4> r = viewport.viewport();
1774 // A negative width or height is an error. A negative x or y is not.
1775 if (r[2] < 0.0f || r[3] < 0.0f)
1776 return;
1777
1778 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
1779 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Viewport;
1780 cmd.args.viewport.x = r[0];
1781 cmd.args.viewport.y = r[1];
1782 cmd.args.viewport.w = r[2];
1783 cmd.args.viewport.h = r[3];
1784 cmd.args.viewport.d0 = viewport.minDepth();
1785 cmd.args.viewport.d1 = viewport.maxDepth();
1786}

1818
1819void QRhiGles2::setStencilRef(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, quint32 refValue)

1899void QRhiGles2::beginExternal(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb)
1900{
1901 if (ofr.active) {
1902 Q_ASSERT(!currentSwapChain);
1903 if (!ensureContext())
1904 return;
1905 } else {
1906 Q_ASSERT(currentSwapChain);
1907 if (!ensureContext(surface: currentSwapChain->surface))
1908 return;
1909 }
1910
1911 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
1912
1913 if (cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePass
1914 && !cbD->computePassState.writtenResources.isEmpty())
1915 {
1916 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
1917 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Barrier;
1918 cmd.args.barrier.barriers = GL_ALL_BARRIER_BITS;
1919 }
1920
1921 executeCommandBuffer(cb: cbD);
1922
1923 cbD->resetCommands();
1924
1925 if (vao) {
1926 f->glBindVertexArray(array: 0);
1927 } else {
1928 f->glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, buffer: 0);
1929 f->glBindBuffer(GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, buffer: 0);
1930 if (caps.compute)
1931 f->glBindBuffer(GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER, buffer: 0);
1932 }
1933}
1934
1935void QRhiGles2::endExternal(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb)
1936{
1937 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
1938 Q_ASSERT(cbD->commands.isEmpty() && cbD->currentPassResTrackerIndex == -1);
1939
1940 cbD->resetCachedState();
1941
1942 if (cbD->recordingPass != QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass) {
1943 // Commands that come after this point need a resource tracker and also
1944 // a BarriersForPass command enqueued. (the ones we had from
1945 // beginPass() are now gone since beginExternal() processed all that
1946 // due to calling executeCommandBuffer()).
1947 enqueueBarriersForPass(cbD);
1948 }
1949
1950 addBoundaryCommand(cbD, type: QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::ResetFrame);
1951
1952 if (cbD->currentTarget)
1953 enqueueBindFramebuffer(rt: cbD->currentTarget, cbD);
1954}
1955
1956QRhi::FrameOpResult QRhiGles2::beginFrame(QRhiSwapChain *swapChain, QRhi::BeginFrameFlags)
1957{
1958 QGles2SwapChain *swapChainD = QRHI_RES(QGles2SwapChain, swapChain);
1959 if (!ensureContext(surface: swapChainD->surface))
1960 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
1961
1962 ctx->handle()->beginFrame();
1963
1964 currentSwapChain = swapChainD;
1965
1966 executeDeferredReleases();
1967 swapChainD->cb.resetState();
1968
1969 addBoundaryCommand(cbD: &swapChainD->cb, type: QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BeginFrame);
1970
1971 return QRhi::FrameOpSuccess;
1972}
1973
1974QRhi::FrameOpResult QRhiGles2::endFrame(QRhiSwapChain *swapChain, QRhi::EndFrameFlags flags)
1975{
1976 QGles2SwapChain *swapChainD = QRHI_RES(QGles2SwapChain, swapChain);
1977 Q_ASSERT(currentSwapChain == swapChainD);
1978
1979 addBoundaryCommand(cbD: &swapChainD->cb, type: QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::EndFrame);
1980
1981 if (!ensureContext(surface: swapChainD->surface))
1982 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
1983
1984 executeCommandBuffer(cb: &swapChainD->cb);
1985
1986 if (swapChainD->surface && !flags.testFlag(flag: QRhi::SkipPresent)) {
1987 ctx->swapBuffers(surface: swapChainD->surface);
1988 needsMakeCurrentDueToSwap = true;
1989 } else {
1990 f->glFlush();
1991 }
1992
1993 swapChainD->frameCount += 1;
1994 currentSwapChain = nullptr;
1995
1996 ctx->handle()->endFrame();
1997
1998 return QRhi::FrameOpSuccess;
1999}
2000
2001QRhi::FrameOpResult QRhiGles2::beginOffscreenFrame(QRhiCommandBuffer **cb, QRhi::BeginFrameFlags)
2002{
2003 if (!ensureContext())
2004 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
2005
2006 ofr.active = true;
2007
2008 executeDeferredReleases();
2009 ofr.cbWrapper.resetState();
2010
2011 addBoundaryCommand(cbD: &ofr.cbWrapper, type: QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BeginFrame);
2012 *cb = &ofr.cbWrapper;
2013
2014 return QRhi::FrameOpSuccess;
2015}
2016
2017QRhi::FrameOpResult QRhiGles2::endOffscreenFrame(QRhi::EndFrameFlags flags)
2018{
2019 Q_UNUSED(flags);
2020 Q_ASSERT(ofr.active);
2021 ofr.active = false;
2022
2023 addBoundaryCommand(cbD: &ofr.cbWrapper, type: QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::EndFrame);
2024
2025 if (!ensureContext())
2026 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
2027
2028 executeCommandBuffer(cb: &ofr.cbWrapper);
2029
2030 // Just as endFrame() does a flush when skipping the swapBuffers(), do it
2031 // here as well. This has the added benefit of playing nice when rendering
2032 // to a texture from a context and then consuming that texture from
2033 // another, sharing context.
2034 f->glFlush();
2035
2036 return QRhi::FrameOpSuccess;
2037}
2038
2039QRhi::FrameOpResult QRhiGles2::finish()
2040{
2041 if (inFrame) {
2042 if (ofr.active) {
2043 Q_ASSERT(!currentSwapChain);
2044 Q_ASSERT(ofr.cbWrapper.recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass);
2045 if (!ensureContext())
2046 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
2047 executeCommandBuffer(cb: &ofr.cbWrapper);
2048 ofr.cbWrapper.resetCommands();
2049 } else {
2050 Q_ASSERT(currentSwapChain);
2051 Q_ASSERT(currentSwapChain->cb.recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass);
2052 if (!ensureContext(surface: currentSwapChain->surface))
2053 return contextLost ? QRhi::FrameOpDeviceLost : QRhi::FrameOpError;
2054 executeCommandBuffer(cb: &currentSwapChain->cb);
2055 currentSwapChain->cb.resetCommands();
2056 }
2057 // Do an actual glFinish(). May seem superfluous, but this is what
2058 // matches most other backends e.g. Vulkan/Metal that do a heavyweight
2059 // wait-for-idle blocking in their finish(). More importantly, this
2060 // allows clients simply call finish() in threaded or shared context
2061 // situations where one explicitly needs to do a glFlush or Finish.
2062 f->glFinish();
2063 }
2064 return QRhi::FrameOpSuccess;
2065}

2082static inline GLbitfield barriersForBuffer()
2083{
2084 return GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BARRIER_BIT
2085 | GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BARRIER_BIT
2086 | GL_UNIFORM_BARRIER_BIT
2087 | GL_BUFFER_UPDATE_BARRIER_BIT
2088 | GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BARRIER_BIT;
2089}
2090
2091static inline GLbitfield barriersForTexture()
2092{
2093 return GL_TEXTURE_FETCH_BARRIER_BIT
2094 | GL_SHADER_IMAGE_ACCESS_BARRIER_BIT
2095 | GL_PIXEL_BUFFER_BARRIER_BIT
2096 | GL_TEXTURE_UPDATE_BARRIER_BIT
2097 | GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BARRIER_BIT;
2098}

2100void QRhiGles2::trackedBufferBarrier(QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD, QGles2Buffer *bufD, QGles2Buffer::Access access)
2101{
2102 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass); // this is for resource updates only
2103 if (!bufD->m_usage.testFlag(flag: QRhiBuffer::StorageBuffer))
2104 return;
2105
2106 const QGles2Buffer::Access prevAccess = bufD->usageState.access;
2107 if (access == prevAccess)
2108 return;
2109
2110 if (bufferAccessIsWrite(access: prevAccess)) {
2111 // Generating the minimal barrier set is way too complicated to do
2112 // correctly (prevAccess is overwritten so we won't have proper
2113 // tracking across multiple passes) so setting all barrier bits will do
2114 // for now.
2115 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
2116 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Barrier;
2117 cmd.args.barrier.barriers = barriersForBuffer();
2118 }
2119
2120 bufD->usageState.access = access;
2121}
2122
2123void QRhiGles2::trackedImageBarrier(QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD, QGles2Texture *texD, QGles2Texture::Access access)
2124{
2125 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass); // this is for resource updates only
2126 if (!texD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::UsedWithLoadStore))
2127 return;
2128
2129 const QGles2Texture::Access prevAccess = texD->usageState.access;
2130 if (access == prevAccess)
2131 return;
2132
2133 if (textureAccessIsWrite(access: prevAccess)) {
2134 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
2135 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Barrier;
2136 cmd.args.barrier.barriers = barriersForTexture();
2137 }
2138
2139 texD->usageState.access = access;
2140}

2336 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, u.dst);
2337 for (int layer = 0, maxLayer = u.subresDesc.size(); layer < maxLayer; ++layer) {
2338 for (int level = 0; level < QRhi::MAX_MIP_LEVELS; ++level) {
2339 for (const QRhiTextureSubresourceUploadDescription &subresDesc : std::as_const(t: u.subresDesc[layer][level]))
2340 enqueueSubresUpload(texD, cbD, layer, level, subresDesc);
2341 }
2342 }
2343 texD->specified = true;
2344 } else if (u.type == QRhiResourceUpdateBatchPrivate::TextureOp::Copy) {
2345 Q_ASSERT(u.src && u.dst);
2346 QGles2Texture *srcD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, u.src);
2347 QGles2Texture *dstD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, u.dst);
2348
2349 trackedImageBarrier(cbD, texD: srcD, access: QGles2Texture::AccessRead);
2350 trackedImageBarrier(cbD, texD: dstD, access: QGles2Texture::AccessUpdate);
2351
2352 const QSize mipSize = q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: u.desc.sourceLevel(), baseLevelSize: srcD->m_pixelSize);
2353 const QSize copySize = u.desc.pixelSize().isEmpty() ? mipSize : u.desc.pixelSize();
2354 // do not translate coordinates, even if sp is bottom-left from gl's pov
2355 const QPoint sp = u.desc.sourceTopLeft();
2356 const QPoint dp = u.desc.destinationTopLeft();
2357
2358 const GLenum srcFaceTargetBase = srcD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap)
2359 ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X : srcD->target;
2360 const GLenum dstFaceTargetBase = dstD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap)
2361 ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X : dstD->target;
2362
2363 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
2364 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::CopyTex;
2365
2366 const bool srcHasZ = srcD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::ThreeDimensional) || srcD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
2367 const bool dstHasZ = dstD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::ThreeDimensional) || dstD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
2368 const bool dstIs1dArray = dstD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::OneDimensional)
2369 && dstD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
2370
2371 cmd.args.copyTex.srcTarget = srcD->target;
2372 cmd.args.copyTex.srcFaceTarget = srcFaceTargetBase + (srcHasZ ? 0u : uint(u.desc.sourceLayer()));
2373 cmd.args.copyTex.srcTexture = srcD->texture;
2374 cmd.args.copyTex.srcLevel = u.desc.sourceLevel();
2375 cmd.args.copyTex.srcX = sp.x();
2376 cmd.args.copyTex.srcY = sp.y();
2377 cmd.args.copyTex.srcZ = srcHasZ ? u.desc.sourceLayer() : 0;
2378
2379 cmd.args.copyTex.dstTarget = dstD->target;
2380 cmd.args.copyTex.dstFaceTarget = dstFaceTargetBase + (dstHasZ ? 0u : uint(u.desc.destinationLayer()));
2381 cmd.args.copyTex.dstTexture = dstD->texture;
2382 cmd.args.copyTex.dstLevel = u.desc.destinationLevel();
2383 cmd.args.copyTex.dstX = dp.x();
2384 cmd.args.copyTex.dstY = dstIs1dArray ? u.desc.destinationLayer() : dp.y();
2385 cmd.args.copyTex.dstZ = dstHasZ ? u.desc.destinationLayer() : 0;
2386
2387 cmd.args.copyTex.w = copySize.width();
2388 cmd.args.copyTex.h = copySize.height();
2389 } else if (u.type == QRhiResourceUpdateBatchPrivate::TextureOp::Read) {
2390 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
2391 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::ReadPixels;
2392 cmd.args.readPixels.result = u.result;
2393 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, u.rb.texture());
2394 if (texD)
2395 trackedImageBarrier(cbD, texD, access: QGles2Texture::AccessRead);
2396 cmd.args.readPixels.texture = texD ? texD->texture : 0;
2397 cmd.args.readPixels.slice3D = -1;
2398 if (texD) {
2399 const QSize readImageSize = q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: u.rb.level(), baseLevelSize: texD->m_pixelSize);
2400 cmd.args.readPixels.w = readImageSize.width();
2401 cmd.args.readPixels.h = readImageSize.height();
2402 cmd.args.readPixels.format = texD->m_format;
2403 if (texD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::ThreeDimensional)
2404 || texD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray))
2405 {
2406 cmd.args.readPixels.readTarget = texD->target;
2407 cmd.args.readPixels.slice3D = u.rb.layer();
2408 } else {
2409 const GLenum faceTargetBase = texD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap)
2410 ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X : texD->target;
2411 cmd.args.readPixels.readTarget = faceTargetBase + uint(u.rb.layer());
2412 }
2413 cmd.args.readPixels.level = u.rb.level();
2414 }
2415 } else if (u.type == QRhiResourceUpdateBatchPrivate::TextureOp::GenMips) {
2416 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, u.dst);
2417 trackedImageBarrier(cbD, texD, access: QGles2Texture::AccessFramebuffer);
2418 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
2419 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::GenMip;
2420 cmd.args.genMip.target = texD->target;
2421 cmd.args.genMip.texture = texD->texture;
2422 }
2423 }
2424
2425 ud->free();
2426}

2746struct CommandBufferExecTrackedState
2747{
2748 GLenum indexType = GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT;
2749 quint32 indexStride = sizeof(quint16);
2750 quint32 indexOffset = 0;
2751 GLuint currentArrayBuffer = 0;
2752 GLuint currentElementArrayBuffer = 0;
2753 struct {
2754 QRhiGraphicsPipeline *ps = nullptr;
2755 GLuint buffer = 0;
2756 quint32 offset = 0;
2757 int binding = 0;
2758 } lastBindVertexBuffer;
2759 static const int TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT = 16;
2760 bool enabledAttribArrays[TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT] = {};
2761 bool nonzeroAttribDivisor[TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT] = {};
2762 bool instancedAttributesUsed = false;
2763 int maxUntrackedInstancedAttribute = 0;
2764};
2765
2766// Helper that must be used in executeCommandBuffer() whenever changing the
2767// ARRAY or ELEMENT_ARRAY buffer binding outside of Command::BindVertexBuffer
2768// and Command::BindIndexBuffer.
2769static inline void bindVertexIndexBufferWithStateReset(CommandBufferExecTrackedState *state,
2770 QOpenGLExtensions *f,
2771 GLenum target,
2772 GLuint buffer)
2773{
2774 state->currentArrayBuffer = 0;
2775 state->currentElementArrayBuffer = 0;
2776 state->lastBindVertexBuffer.buffer = 0;
2777 f->glBindBuffer(target, buffer);
2778}
2779
2780void QRhiGles2::executeCommandBuffer(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb)
2781{
2782 CommandBufferExecTrackedState state;
2783 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
2784
2785 for (auto it = cbD->commands.cbegin(), end = cbD->commands.cend(); it != end; ++it) {
2786 const QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(*it);
2787 switch (cmd.cmd) {
2788 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BeginFrame:
2789 if (caps.coreProfile) {
2790 if (!vao)
2791 f->glGenVertexArrays(n: 1, arrays: &vao);
2792 f->glBindVertexArray(array: vao);
2793 }
2794 break;
2795 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::EndFrame:
2796 if (state.instancedAttributesUsed) {
2797 for (int i = 0; i < CommandBufferExecTrackedState::TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT; ++i) {
2798 if (state.nonzeroAttribDivisor[i])
2799 f->glVertexAttribDivisor(index: GLuint(i), divisor: 0);
2800 }
2801 for (int i = CommandBufferExecTrackedState::TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT; i <= state.maxUntrackedInstancedAttribute; ++i)
2802 f->glVertexAttribDivisor(index: GLuint(i), divisor: 0);
2803 state.instancedAttributesUsed = false;
2804 }
2805#ifdef Q_OS_WASM
2806 for (int i = 0; i < CommandBufferExecTrackedState::TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT; ++i) {
2807 if (state.enabledAttribArrays[i]) {
2808 f->glDisableVertexAttribArray(GLuint(i));
2809 state.enabledAttribArrays[i] = false;
2810 }
2811 }
2812#endif
2813 if (vao)
2814 f->glBindVertexArray(array: 0);
2815 break;
2816 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::ResetFrame:
2817 if (vao)
2818 f->glBindVertexArray(array: vao);
2819 break;
2820 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Viewport:
2821 f->glViewport(x: GLint(cmd.args.viewport.x), y: GLint(cmd.args.viewport.y), width: GLsizei(cmd.args.viewport.w), height: GLsizei(cmd.args.viewport.h));
2822 f->glDepthRangef(zNear: cmd.args.viewport.d0, zFar: cmd.args.viewport.d1);
2823 break;
2824 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Scissor:
2825 f->glScissor(x: cmd.args.scissor.x, y: cmd.args.scissor.y, width: cmd.args.scissor.w, height: cmd.args.scissor.h);
2826 break;
2827 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BlendConstants:
2828 f->glBlendColor(red: cmd.args.blendConstants.r, green: cmd.args.blendConstants.g, blue: cmd.args.blendConstants.b, alpha: cmd.args.blendConstants.a);
2829 break;
2830 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::StencilRef:
2831 {
2832 QGles2GraphicsPipeline *psD = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, cmd.args.stencilRef.ps);
2833 if (psD) {
2834 const GLint ref = GLint(cmd.args.stencilRef.ref);
2835 f->glStencilFuncSeparate(GL_FRONT, func: toGlCompareOp(op: psD->m_stencilFront.compareOp), ref, mask: psD->m_stencilReadMask);
2836 f->glStencilFuncSeparate(GL_BACK, func: toGlCompareOp(op: psD->m_stencilBack.compareOp), ref, mask: psD->m_stencilReadMask);
2837 cbD->graphicsPassState.dynamic.stencilRef = ref;
2838 } else {
2839 qWarning(msg: "No graphics pipeline active for setStencilRef; ignored");
2840 }
2841 }
2842 break;
2843 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindVertexBuffer:
2844 {
2845 QGles2GraphicsPipeline *psD = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.ps);
2846 if (psD) {
2847 if (state.lastBindVertexBuffer.ps == psD
2848 && state.lastBindVertexBuffer.buffer == cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.buffer
2849 && state.lastBindVertexBuffer.offset == cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.offset
2850 && state.lastBindVertexBuffer.binding == cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.binding)
2851 {
2852 // The pipeline and so the vertex input layout is
2853 // immutable, no point in issuing the exact same set of
2854 // glVertexAttribPointer again and again for the same buffer.
2855 break;
2856 }
2857 state.lastBindVertexBuffer.ps = psD;
2858 state.lastBindVertexBuffer.buffer = cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.buffer;
2859 state.lastBindVertexBuffer.offset = cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.offset;
2860 state.lastBindVertexBuffer.binding = cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.binding;
2861
2862 if (cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.buffer != state.currentArrayBuffer) {
2863 state.currentArrayBuffer = cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.buffer;
2864 // we do not support more than one vertex buffer
2865 f->glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, buffer: state.currentArrayBuffer);
2866 }
2867 for (auto it = psD->m_vertexInputLayout.cbeginAttributes(), itEnd = psD->m_vertexInputLayout.cendAttributes();
2868 it != itEnd; ++it)
2869 {
2870 const int bindingIdx = it->binding();
2871 if (bindingIdx != cmd.args.bindVertexBuffer.binding)
2872 continue;
2873
2874 const QRhiVertexInputBinding *inputBinding = psD->m_vertexInputLayout.bindingAt(index: bindingIdx);
2875 const int stride = int(inputBinding->stride());
2876 int size = 1;
2877 GLenum type = GL_FLOAT;
2878 bool normalize = false;
2879 switch (it->format()) {
2880 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::Float4:
2881 type = GL_FLOAT;
2882 size = 4;
2883 break;
2884 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::Float3:
2885 type = GL_FLOAT;
2886 size = 3;
2887 break;
2888 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::Float2:
2889 type = GL_FLOAT;
2890 size = 2;
2891 break;
2892 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::Float:
2893 type = GL_FLOAT;
2894 size = 1;
2895 break;
2896 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::UNormByte4:
2897 type = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
2898 normalize = true;
2899 size = 4;
2900 break;
2901 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::UNormByte2:
2902 type = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
2903 normalize = true;
2904 size = 2;
2905 break;
2906 case QRhiVertexInputAttribute::UNormByte:

3341 f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_READ_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0,
3342 GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbuffer: cmd.args.blitFromRb.renderbuffer);
3343 f->glBindFramebuffer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, framebuffer: fbo[1]);
3344 if (cmd.args.blitFromRb.target == GL_TEXTURE_3D || cmd.args.blitFromRb.target == GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY) {
3345 f->glFramebufferTextureLayer(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0,
3346 texture: cmd.args.blitFromRb.texture, level: cmd.args.blitFromRb.dstLevel, layer: cmd.args.blitFromRb.dstLayer);
3347 } else {
3348 f->glFramebufferTexture2D(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0, textarget: cmd.args.blitFromRb.target,
3349 texture: cmd.args.blitFromRb.texture, level: cmd.args.blitFromRb.dstLevel);
3350 }
3351 f->glBlitFramebuffer(srcX0: 0, srcY0: 0, srcX1: cmd.args.blitFromRb.w, srcY1: cmd.args.blitFromRb.h,
3352 dstX0: 0, dstY0: 0, dstX1: cmd.args.blitFromRb.w, dstY1: cmd.args.blitFromRb.h,
3353 GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT,
3354 GL_LINEAR);
3355 f->glBindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, framebuffer: ctx->defaultFramebufferObject());
3356 f->glDeleteFramebuffers(n: 2, framebuffers: fbo);
3357 }
3358 break;
3359 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::GenMip:
3360 f->glBindTexture(target: cmd.args.genMip.target, texture: cmd.args.genMip.texture);
3361 f->glGenerateMipmap(target: cmd.args.genMip.target);
3362 break;
3363 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindComputePipeline:
3364 {
3365 QGles2ComputePipeline *psD = QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, cmd.args.bindComputePipeline.ps);
3366 f->glUseProgram(program: psD->program);
3367 }
3368 break;
3369 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Dispatch:
3370 f->glDispatchCompute(num_groups_x: cmd.args.dispatch.x, num_groups_y: cmd.args.dispatch.y, num_groups_z: cmd.args.dispatch.z);
3371 break;
3372 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BarriersForPass:
3373 {
3374 if (!caps.compute)
3375 break;
3376 GLbitfield barriers = 0;
3377 QRhiPassResourceTracker &tracker(cbD->passResTrackers[cmd.args.barriersForPass.trackerIndex]);
3378 // we only care about after-write, not any other accesses, and
3379 // cannot tell if something was written in a shader several passes
3380 // ago: now the previously written resource may be used with an
3381 // access that was not in the previous passes, result in a missing
3382 // barrier in theory. Hence setting all barrier bits whenever
3383 // something previously written is used for the first time in a
3384 // subsequent pass.
3385 for (auto it = tracker.cbeginBuffers(), itEnd = tracker.cendBuffers(); it != itEnd; ++it) {
3386 QGles2Buffer::Access accessBeforePass = QGles2Buffer::Access(it->stateAtPassBegin.access);
3387 if (bufferAccessIsWrite(access: accessBeforePass))
3388 barriers |= barriersForBuffer();
3389 }
3390 for (auto it = tracker.cbeginTextures(), itEnd = tracker.cendTextures(); it != itEnd; ++it) {
3391 QGles2Texture::Access accessBeforePass = QGles2Texture::Access(it->stateAtPassBegin.access);
3392 if (textureAccessIsWrite(access: accessBeforePass))
3393 barriers |= barriersForTexture();
3394 }
3395 if (barriers)
3396 f->glMemoryBarrier(barriers);
3397 }
3398 break;
3399 case QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Barrier:
3400 if (caps.compute)
3401 f->glMemoryBarrier(barriers: cmd.args.barrier.barriers);
3402 break;
3403 default:
3404 break;
3405 }
3406 }
3407 if (state.instancedAttributesUsed) {
3408 for (int i = 0; i < CommandBufferExecTrackedState::TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT; ++i) {
3409 if (state.nonzeroAttribDivisor[i])
3410 f->glVertexAttribDivisor(index: GLuint(i), divisor: 0);
3411 }
3412 for (int i = CommandBufferExecTrackedState::TRACKED_ATTRIB_COUNT; i <= state.maxUntrackedInstancedAttribute; ++i)
3413 f->glVertexAttribDivisor(index: GLuint(i), divisor: 0);
3414 }
3415}

3608template <typename T>
3609static inline void qrhi_std140_to_packed(T *dst, int vecSize, int elemCount, const void *src)
3610{
3611 const T *p = reinterpret_cast<const T *>(src);
3612 for (int i = 0; i < elemCount; ++i) {
3613 for (int j = 0; j < vecSize; ++j)
3614 dst[vecSize * i + j] = *p++;
3615 p += 4 - vecSize;
3616 }
3617}
