3619void QRhiGles2::bindCombinedSampler(QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD, QGles2Texture *texD, QGles2Sampler *samplerD,
3620 void *ps, uint psGeneration, int glslLocation,
3621 int *texUnit, bool *activeTexUnitAltered)
3622{
3623 const bool samplerStateValid = texD->samplerState == samplerD->d;
3624 const bool cachedStateInRange = *texUnit < 16;
3625 bool updateTextureBinding = true;
3626 if (samplerStateValid && cachedStateInRange) {
3627 // If we already encountered the same texture with
3628 // the same pipeline for this texture unit in the
3629 // current pass, then the shader program already
3630 // has the uniform set. As in a 3D scene one model
3631 // often has more than one associated texture map,
3632 // the savings here can become significant,
3633 // depending on the scene.
3634 if (cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].ps == ps
3635 && cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].psGeneration == psGeneration
3636 && cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].texture == texD->texture)
3637 {
3638 updateTextureBinding = false;
3639 }
3640 }
3641 if (updateTextureBinding) {
3642 f->glActiveTexture(GL_TEXTURE0 + uint(*texUnit));
3643 *activeTexUnitAltered = true;
3644 f->glBindTexture(target: texD->target, texture: texD->texture);
3645 f->glUniform1i(location: glslLocation, x: *texUnit);
3646 if (cachedStateInRange) {
3647 cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].ps = ps;
3648 cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].psGeneration = psGeneration;
3649 cbD->textureUnitState[*texUnit].texture = texD->texture;
3650 }
3651 }
3652 ++(*texUnit);
3653 if (!samplerStateValid) {
3654 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, param: GLint(samplerD->d.glminfilter));
3655 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, param: GLint(samplerD->d.glmagfilter));
3656 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S, param: GLint(samplerD->d.glwraps));
3657 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T, param: GLint(samplerD->d.glwrapt));
3658 if (caps.texture3D)
3659 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R, param: GLint(samplerD->d.glwrapr));
3660 if (caps.textureCompareMode) {
3661 if (samplerD->d.gltexcomparefunc != GL_NEVER) {
3662 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE, GL_COMPARE_REF_TO_TEXTURE);
3663 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC, param: GLint(samplerD->d.gltexcomparefunc));
3664 } else {
3665 f->glTexParameteri(target: texD->target, GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE, GL_NONE);
3666 }
3667 }
3668 texD->samplerState = samplerD->d;
3669 }
3670}
3671
3672void QRhiGles2::bindShaderResources(QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD,
3673 QRhiGraphicsPipeline *maybeGraphicsPs, QRhiComputePipeline *maybeComputePs,
3674 QRhiShaderResourceBindings *srb,
3675 const uint *dynOfsPairs, int dynOfsCount)
3676{
3677 QGles2ShaderResourceBindings *srbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2ShaderResourceBindings, srb);
3678 int texUnit = 1; // start from unit 1, keep 0 for resource mgmt stuff to avoid clashes
3679 bool activeTexUnitAltered = false;
3680 union data32_t {
3681 float f;
3682 qint32 i;
3683 };
3684 QVarLengthArray<data32_t, 256> packedArray;
3685 QGles2UniformDescriptionVector &uniforms(maybeGraphicsPs ? QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->uniforms
3686 : QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->uniforms);
3687 QGles2UniformState *uniformState = maybeGraphicsPs ? QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->uniformState
3688 : QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->uniformState;
3689 struct SeparateTexture {
3690 QGles2Texture *texture;
3691 int binding;
3692 int elem;
3693 };
3694 QVarLengthArray<SeparateTexture, 8> separateTextureBindings;
3695 struct SeparateSampler {
3696 QGles2Sampler *sampler;
3697 int binding;
3698 };
3699 QVarLengthArray<SeparateSampler, 4> separateSamplerBindings;
3700
3701 for (int i = 0, ie = srbD->m_bindings.size(); i != ie; ++i) {
3702 const QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Data *b = srbD->m_bindings.at(idx: i).data();
3703
3704 switch (b->type) {
3705 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::UniformBuffer:
3706 {
3707 int viewOffset = b->u.ubuf.offset;
3708 for (int j = 0; j < dynOfsCount; ++j) {
3709 if (dynOfsPairs[2 * j] == uint(b->binding)) {
3710 viewOffset = int(dynOfsPairs[2 * j + 1]);
3711 break;
3712 }
3713 }
3714 QGles2Buffer *bufD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Buffer, b->u.ubuf.buf);
3715 const char *bufView = bufD->data.constData() + viewOffset;
3716 for (const QGles2UniformDescription &uniform : std::as_const(t&: uniforms)) {
3717 if (uniform.binding == b->binding) {
3718 // in a uniform buffer everything is at least 4 byte aligned
3719 // so this should not cause unaligned reads
3720 const void *src = bufView + uniform.offset;
3721
3722#ifndef QT_NO_DEBUG
3723 if (uniform.arrayDim > 0
3724 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Float
3725 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Vec2
3726 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Vec3
3727 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Vec4
3728 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Int
3729 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Int2
3730 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Int3
3731 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Int4
3732 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Mat3
3733 && uniform.type != QShaderDescription::Mat4)
3734 {
3735 qWarning("Uniform with buffer binding %d, buffer offset %d, type %d is an array, "
3736 "but arrays are only supported for float, vec2, vec3, vec4, int, "
3737 "ivec2, ivec3, ivec4, mat3 and mat4. "
3738 "Only the first element will be set.",
3739 uniform.binding, uniform.offset, uniform.type);
3740 }
3741#endif
3742
3743 // Our input is an std140 layout uniform block. See
3744 // "Standard Uniform Block Layout" in section 7.6.2.2 of
3745 // the OpenGL spec. This has some peculiar alignment
3746 // requirements, which is not what glUniform* wants. Hence
3747 // the unpacking/repacking for arrays and certain types.
3748
3749 switch (uniform.type) {
3750 case QShaderDescription::Float:
3751 {
3752 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3753 if (elemCount < 1) {
3754 const float v = *reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src);
3755 if (uniform.glslLocation <= QGles2UniformState::MAX_TRACKED_LOCATION) {
3756 QGles2UniformState &thisUniformState(uniformState[uniform.glslLocation]);
3757 if (thisUniformState.componentCount != 1 || thisUniformState.v[0] != v) {
3758 thisUniformState.componentCount = 1;
3759 thisUniformState.v[0] = v;
3760 f->glUniform1f(location: uniform.glslLocation, x: v);
3761 }
3762 } else {
3763 f->glUniform1f(location: uniform.glslLocation, x: v);
3764 }
3765 } else {
3766 // input is 16 bytes per element as per std140, have to convert to packed
3767 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount);
3768 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->f, vecSize: 1, elemCount, src);
3769 f->glUniform1fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->f);
3770 }
3771 }
3772 break;
3773 case QShaderDescription::Vec2:
3774 {
3775 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3776 if (elemCount < 1) {
3777 const float *v = reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src);
3778 if (uniform.glslLocation <= QGles2UniformState::MAX_TRACKED_LOCATION) {
3779 QGles2UniformState &thisUniformState(uniformState[uniform.glslLocation]);
3780 if (thisUniformState.componentCount != 2
3781 || thisUniformState.v[0] != v[0]
3782 || thisUniformState.v[1] != v[1])
3783 {
3784 thisUniformState.componentCount = 2;
3785 thisUniformState.v[0] = v[0];
3786 thisUniformState.v[1] = v[1];
3787 f->glUniform2fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3788 }
3789 } else {
3790 f->glUniform2fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3791 }
3792 } else {
3793 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount * 2);
3794 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->f, vecSize: 2, elemCount, src);
3795 f->glUniform2fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->f);
3796 }
3797 }
3798 break;
3799 case QShaderDescription::Vec3:
3800 {
3801 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3802 if (elemCount < 1) {
3803 const float *v = reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src);
3804 if (uniform.glslLocation <= QGles2UniformState::MAX_TRACKED_LOCATION) {
3805 QGles2UniformState &thisUniformState(uniformState[uniform.glslLocation]);
3806 if (thisUniformState.componentCount != 3
3807 || thisUniformState.v[0] != v[0]
3808 || thisUniformState.v[1] != v[1]
3809 || thisUniformState.v[2] != v[2])
3810 {
3811 thisUniformState.componentCount = 3;
3812 thisUniformState.v[0] = v[0];
3813 thisUniformState.v[1] = v[1];
3814 thisUniformState.v[2] = v[2];
3815 f->glUniform3fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3816 }
3817 } else {
3818 f->glUniform3fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3819 }
3820 } else {
3821 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount * 3);
3822 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->f, vecSize: 3, elemCount, src);
3823 f->glUniform3fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->f);
3824 }
3825 }
3826 break;
3827 case QShaderDescription::Vec4:
3828 {
3829 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3830 if (elemCount < 1) {
3831 const float *v = reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src);
3832 if (uniform.glslLocation <= QGles2UniformState::MAX_TRACKED_LOCATION) {
3833 QGles2UniformState &thisUniformState(uniformState[uniform.glslLocation]);
3834 if (thisUniformState.componentCount != 4
3835 || thisUniformState.v[0] != v[0]
3836 || thisUniformState.v[1] != v[1]
3837 || thisUniformState.v[2] != v[2]
3838 || thisUniformState.v[3] != v[3])
3839 {
3840 thisUniformState.componentCount = 4;
3841 thisUniformState.v[0] = v[0];
3842 thisUniformState.v[1] = v[1];
3843 thisUniformState.v[2] = v[2];
3844 thisUniformState.v[3] = v[3];
3845 f->glUniform4fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3846 }
3847 } else {
3848 f->glUniform4fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v);
3849 }
3850 } else {
3851 f->glUniform4fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src));
3852 }
3853 }
3854 break;
3855 case QShaderDescription::Mat2:
3856 f->glUniformMatrix2fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, GL_FALSE, value: reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src));
3857 break;
3858 case QShaderDescription::Mat3:
3859 {
3860 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3861 if (elemCount < 1) {
3862 // 4 floats per column (or row, if row-major)
3863 float mat[9];
3864 const float *srcMat = reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src);
3865 memcpy(dest: mat, src: srcMat, n: 3 * sizeof(float));
3866 memcpy(dest: mat + 3, src: srcMat + 4, n: 3 * sizeof(float));
3867 memcpy(dest: mat + 6, src: srcMat + 8, n: 3 * sizeof(float));
3868 f->glUniformMatrix3fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, GL_FALSE, value: mat);
3869 } else {
3870 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount * 9);
3871 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->f, vecSize: 3, elemCount: elemCount * 3, src);
3872 f->glUniformMatrix3fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, GL_FALSE, value: &packedArray.constData()->f);
3873 }
3874 }
3875 break;
3876 case QShaderDescription::Mat4:
3877 f->glUniformMatrix4fv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: qMax(a: 1, b: uniform.arrayDim), GL_FALSE, value: reinterpret_cast<const float *>(src));
3878 break;
3879 case QShaderDescription::Int:
3880 {
3881 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3882 if (elemCount < 1) {
3883 f->glUniform1i(location: uniform.glslLocation, x: *reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3884 } else {
3885 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount);
3886 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->i, vecSize: 1, elemCount, src);
3887 f->glUniform1iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->i);
3888 }
3889 }
3890 break;
3891 case QShaderDescription::Int2:
3892 {
3893 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3894 if (elemCount < 1) {
3895 f->glUniform2iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3896 } else {
3897 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount * 2);
3898 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->i, vecSize: 2, elemCount, src);
3899 f->glUniform2iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->i);
3900 }
3901 }
3902 break;
3903 case QShaderDescription::Int3:
3904 {
3905 const int elemCount = uniform.arrayDim;
3906 if (elemCount < 1) {
3907 f->glUniform3iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3908 } else {
3909 packedArray.resize(sz: elemCount * 3);
3910 qrhi_std140_to_packed(dst: &packedArray.data()->i, vecSize: 3, elemCount, src);
3911 f->glUniform3iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: elemCount, v: &packedArray.constData()->i);
3912 }
3913 }
3914 break;
3915 case QShaderDescription::Int4:
3916 f->glUniform4iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: qMax(a: 1, b: uniform.arrayDim), v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3917 break;
3918 case QShaderDescription::Uint:
3919 f->glUniform1ui(location: uniform.glslLocation, v0: *reinterpret_cast<const quint32 *>(src));
3920 break;
3921 case QShaderDescription::Uint2:
3922 f->glUniform2uiv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, value: reinterpret_cast<const quint32 *>(src));
3923 break;
3924 case QShaderDescription::Uint3:
3925 f->glUniform3uiv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, value: reinterpret_cast<const quint32 *>(src));
3926 break;
3927 case QShaderDescription::Uint4:
3928 f->glUniform4uiv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, value: reinterpret_cast<const quint32 *>(src));
3929 break;
3930 case QShaderDescription::Bool: // a glsl bool is 4 bytes, like (u)int
3931 f->glUniform1i(location: uniform.glslLocation, x: *reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3932 break;
3933 case QShaderDescription::Bool2:
3934 f->glUniform2iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3935 break;
3936 case QShaderDescription::Bool3:
3937 f->glUniform3iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3938 break;
3939 case QShaderDescription::Bool4:
3940 f->glUniform4iv(location: uniform.glslLocation, count: 1, v: reinterpret_cast<const qint32 *>(src));
3941 break;
3942 default:
3943 qWarning(msg: "Uniform with buffer binding %d, buffer offset %d has unsupported type %d",
3944 uniform.binding, uniform.offset, uniform.type);
3945 break;
3946 }
3947 }
3948 }
3949 }
3950 break;
3951 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::SampledTexture:
3952 {
3953 const QGles2SamplerDescriptionVector &samplers(maybeGraphicsPs ? QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->samplers
3954 : QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->samplers);
3955 void *ps;
3956 uint psGeneration;
3957 if (maybeGraphicsPs) {
3958 ps = maybeGraphicsPs;
3959 psGeneration = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->generation;
3960 } else {
3961 ps = maybeComputePs;
3962 psGeneration = QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->generation;
3963 }
3964 for (int elem = 0; elem < b->u.stex.count; ++elem) {
3965 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, b->u.stex.texSamplers[elem].tex);
3966 QGles2Sampler *samplerD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Sampler, b->u.stex.texSamplers[elem].sampler);
3967 for (const QGles2SamplerDescription &shaderSampler : samplers) {
3968 if (shaderSampler.combinedBinding == b->binding) {
3969 const int loc = shaderSampler.glslLocation + elem;
3970 bindCombinedSampler(cbD, texD, samplerD, ps, psGeneration, glslLocation: loc, texUnit: &texUnit, activeTexUnitAltered: &activeTexUnitAltered);
3971 break;
3972 }
3973 }
3974 }
3975 }
3976 break;
3977 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Texture:
3978 for (int elem = 0; elem < b->u.stex.count; ++elem) {
3979 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, b->u.stex.texSamplers[elem].tex);
3980 separateTextureBindings.append(t: { .texture: texD, .binding: b->binding, .elem: elem });
3981 }
3982 break;
3983 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Sampler:
3984 {
3985 QGles2Sampler *samplerD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Sampler, b->u.stex.texSamplers[0].sampler);
3986 separateSamplerBindings.append(t: { .sampler: samplerD, .binding: b->binding });
3987 }
3988 break;
3989 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad:
3990 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore:
3991 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoadStore:
3992 {
3993 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, b->u.simage.tex);
3994 Q_ASSERT(texD->m_flags.testFlag(QRhiTexture::UsedWithLoadStore));
3995 const bool layered = texD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap);
3996 GLenum access = GL_READ_WRITE;
3997 if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad)
3998 access = GL_READ_ONLY;
3999 else if (b->type == QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore)
4000 access = GL_WRITE_ONLY;
4001 f->glBindImageTexture(unit: GLuint(b->binding), texture: texD->texture,
4002 level: b->u.simage.level, layered, layer: 0,
4003 access, format: texD->glsizedintformat);
4004 }
4005 break;
4006 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoad:
4007 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferStore:
4008 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoadStore:
4009 {
4010 QGles2Buffer *bufD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Buffer, b->u.sbuf.buf);
4011 Q_ASSERT(bufD->m_usage.testFlag(QRhiBuffer::StorageBuffer));
4012 if (b->u.sbuf.offset == 0 && b->u.sbuf.maybeSize == 0)
4013 f->glBindBufferBase(GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER, index: GLuint(b->binding), buffer: bufD->buffer);
4014 else
4015 f->glBindBufferRange(GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BUFFER, index: GLuint(b->binding), buffer: bufD->buffer,
4016 offset: b->u.sbuf.offset, size: b->u.sbuf.maybeSize ? b->u.sbuf.maybeSize : bufD->m_size);
4017 }
4018 break;
4019 default:
4020 Q_UNREACHABLE();
4021 break;
4022 }
4023 }
4024
4025 if (!separateTextureBindings.isEmpty() || !separateSamplerBindings.isEmpty()) {
4026 const QGles2SamplerDescriptionVector &samplers(maybeGraphicsPs ? QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->samplers
4027 : QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->samplers);
4028 void *ps;
4029 uint psGeneration;
4030 if (maybeGraphicsPs) {
4031 ps = maybeGraphicsPs;
4032 psGeneration = QRHI_RES(QGles2GraphicsPipeline, maybeGraphicsPs)->generation;
4033 } else {
4034 ps = maybeComputePs;
4035 psGeneration = QRHI_RES(QGles2ComputePipeline, maybeComputePs)->generation;
4036 }
4037 for (const QGles2SamplerDescription &shaderSampler : samplers) {
4038 if (shaderSampler.combinedBinding >= 0)
4039 continue;
4040 for (const SeparateSampler &sepSampler : separateSamplerBindings) {
4041 if (sepSampler.binding != shaderSampler.sbinding)
4042 continue;
4043 for (const SeparateTexture &sepTex : separateTextureBindings) {
4044 if (sepTex.binding != shaderSampler.tbinding)
4045 continue;
4046 const int loc = shaderSampler.glslLocation + sepTex.elem;
4047 bindCombinedSampler(cbD, texD: sepTex.texture, samplerD: sepSampler.sampler, ps, psGeneration,
4048 glslLocation: loc, texUnit: &texUnit, activeTexUnitAltered: &activeTexUnitAltered);
4049 }
4050 }
4051 }
4052 }
4053
4054 if (activeTexUnitAltered)
4055 f->glActiveTexture(GL_TEXTURE0);
4056}

4065QGles2RenderTargetData *QRhiGles2::enqueueBindFramebuffer(QRhiRenderTarget *rt, QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD,
4066 bool *wantsColorClear, bool *wantsDsClear)
4067{
4068 QGles2RenderTargetData *rtD = nullptr;
4069 QRhiPassResourceTracker &passResTracker(cbD->passResTrackers[cbD->currentPassResTrackerIndex]);
4070
4071 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &fbCmd(cbD->commands.get());
4072 fbCmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BindFramebuffer;
4073
4074 static const bool doClearBuffers = qEnvironmentVariableIntValue(varName: "QT_GL_NO_CLEAR_BUFFERS") == 0;
4075 static const bool doClearColorBuffer = qEnvironmentVariableIntValue(varName: "QT_GL_NO_CLEAR_COLOR_BUFFER") == 0;
4076
4077 switch (rt->resourceType()) {
4078 case QRhiResource::SwapChainRenderTarget:
4079 rtD = &QRHI_RES(QGles2SwapChainRenderTarget, rt)->d;
4080 if (wantsColorClear)
4081 *wantsColorClear = doClearBuffers && doClearColorBuffer;
4082 if (wantsDsClear)
4083 *wantsDsClear = doClearBuffers;
4084 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.fbo = 0;
4085 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.colorAttCount = 1;
4086 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.stereo = rtD->stereoTarget.has_value();
4087 if (fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.stereo)
4088 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.stereoTarget = rtD->stereoTarget.value();
4089 break;
4090 case QRhiResource::TextureRenderTarget:
4091 {
4092 QGles2TextureRenderTarget *rtTex = QRHI_RES(QGles2TextureRenderTarget, rt);
4093 rtD = &rtTex->d;
4094 if (wantsColorClear)
4095 *wantsColorClear = !rtTex->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTextureRenderTarget::PreserveColorContents);
4096 if (wantsDsClear)
4097 *wantsDsClear = !rtTex->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTextureRenderTarget::PreserveDepthStencilContents);
4098 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.fbo = rtTex->framebuffer;
4099 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.colorAttCount = rtD->colorAttCount;
4100 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.stereo = false;
4101
4102 for (auto it = rtTex->m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments(), itEnd = rtTex->m_desc.cendColorAttachments();
4103 it != itEnd; ++it)
4104 {
4105 const QRhiColorAttachment &colorAtt(*it);
4106 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, colorAtt.texture());
4107 QGles2Texture *resolveTexD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, colorAtt.resolveTexture());
4108 if (texD && cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
4109 trackedRegisterTexture(passResTracker: &passResTracker, texD,
4110 access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexColorOutput,
4111 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexColorOutputStage);
4112 }
4113 if (resolveTexD && cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
4114 trackedRegisterTexture(passResTracker: &passResTracker, texD: resolveTexD,
4115 access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexColorOutput,
4116 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexColorOutputStage);
4117 }
4118 // renderbuffers cannot be written in shaders (no image store) so
4119 // they do not matter here
4120 }
4121 if (rtTex->m_desc.depthTexture() && cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking) {
4122 trackedRegisterTexture(passResTracker: &passResTracker, QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, rtTex->m_desc.depthTexture()),
4123 access: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexDepthOutput,
4124 stage: QRhiPassResourceTracker::TexDepthOutputStage);
4125 }
4126 }
4127 break;
4128 default:
4129 Q_UNREACHABLE();
4130 break;
4131 }
4132
4133 fbCmd.args.bindFramebuffer.srgb = rtD->srgbUpdateAndBlend;
4134
4135 return rtD;
4136}

4147void QRhiGles2::beginPass(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb,
4148 QRhiRenderTarget *rt,
4149 const QColor &colorClearValue,
4150 const QRhiDepthStencilClearValue &depthStencilClearValue,
4151 QRhiResourceUpdateBatch *resourceUpdates,
4152 QRhiCommandBuffer::BeginPassFlags flags)
4153{
4154 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
4155 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass);
4156
4157 if (resourceUpdates)
4158 enqueueResourceUpdates(cb, resourceUpdates);
4159
4160 // Get a new resource tracker. Then add a command that will generate
4161 // glMemoryBarrier() calls based on that tracker when submitted.
4162 enqueueBarriersForPass(cbD);
4163
4164 if (rt->resourceType() == QRhiRenderTarget::TextureRenderTarget) {
4165 QGles2TextureRenderTarget *rtTex = QRHI_RES(QGles2TextureRenderTarget, rt);
4166 if (!QRhiRenderTargetAttachmentTracker::isUpToDate<QGles2Texture, QGles2RenderBuffer>(desc: rtTex->description(), currentResIdList: rtTex->d.currentResIdList))
4167 rtTex->create();
4168 }
4169
4170 bool wantsColorClear, wantsDsClear;
4171 QGles2RenderTargetData *rtD = enqueueBindFramebuffer(rt, cbD, wantsColorClear: &wantsColorClear, wantsDsClear: &wantsDsClear);
4172
4173 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &clearCmd(cbD->commands.get());
4174 clearCmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Clear;
4175 clearCmd.args.clear.mask = 0;
4176 if (rtD->colorAttCount && wantsColorClear)
4177 clearCmd.args.clear.mask |= GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
4178 if (rtD->dsAttCount && wantsDsClear)
4179 clearCmd.args.clear.mask |= GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT | GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
4180 clearCmd.args.clear.c[0] = float(colorClearValue.redF());
4181 clearCmd.args.clear.c[1] = float(colorClearValue.greenF());
4182 clearCmd.args.clear.c[2] = float(colorClearValue.blueF());
4183 clearCmd.args.clear.c[3] = float(colorClearValue.alphaF());
4184 clearCmd.args.clear.d = depthStencilClearValue.depthClearValue();
4185 clearCmd.args.clear.s = depthStencilClearValue.stencilClearValue();
4186
4187 cbD->recordingPass = QGles2CommandBuffer::RenderPass;
4188 cbD->passNeedsResourceTracking = !flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiCommandBuffer::DoNotTrackResourcesForCompute);
4189 cbD->currentTarget = rt;
4190
4191 cbD->resetCachedState();
4192}

4194void QRhiGles2::endPass(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, QRhiResourceUpdateBatch *resourceUpdates)
4195{
4196 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
4197 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::RenderPass);
4198
4199 if (cbD->currentTarget->resourceType() == QRhiResource::TextureRenderTarget) {
4200 QGles2TextureRenderTarget *rtTex = QRHI_RES(QGles2TextureRenderTarget, cbD->currentTarget);
4201 if (rtTex->m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments() != rtTex->m_desc.cendColorAttachments()) {
4202 // handle only 1 color attachment and only (msaa) renderbuffer
4203 const QRhiColorAttachment &colorAtt(*rtTex->m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments());
4204 if (colorAtt.resolveTexture()) {
4205 Q_ASSERT(colorAtt.renderBuffer());
4206 QGles2RenderBuffer *rbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2RenderBuffer, colorAtt.renderBuffer());
4207 const QSize size = colorAtt.resolveTexture()->pixelSize();
4208 if (rbD->pixelSize() != size) {
4209 qWarning(msg: "Resolve source (%dx%d) and target (%dx%d) size does not match",
4210 rbD->pixelSize().width(), rbD->pixelSize().height(), size.width(), size.height());
4211 }
4212 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
4213 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::BlitFromRenderbuffer;
4214 cmd.args.blitFromRb.renderbuffer = rbD->renderbuffer;
4215 cmd.args.blitFromRb.w = size.width();
4216 cmd.args.blitFromRb.h = size.height();
4217 QGles2Texture *colorTexD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, colorAtt.resolveTexture());
4218 if (colorTexD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap))
4219 cmd.args.blitFromRb.target = GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X + uint(colorAtt.resolveLayer());
4220 else
4221 cmd.args.blitFromRb.target = colorTexD->target;
4222 cmd.args.blitFromRb.texture = colorTexD->texture;
4223 cmd.args.blitFromRb.dstLevel = colorAtt.resolveLevel();
4224 const bool hasZ = colorTexD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::ThreeDimensional)
4225 || colorTexD->m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
4226 cmd.args.blitFromRb.dstLayer = hasZ ? colorAtt.resolveLayer() : 0;
4227 }
4228 }
4229 }
4230
4231 cbD->recordingPass = QGles2CommandBuffer::NoPass;
4232 cbD->currentTarget = nullptr;
4233
4234 if (resourceUpdates)
4235 enqueueResourceUpdates(cb, resourceUpdates);
4236}

4284template<typename T>
4285inline void qrhigl_accumulateComputeResource(T *writtenResources, QRhiResource *resource,
4286 QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Type bindingType,
4287 int loadTypeVal, int storeTypeVal, int loadStoreTypeVal)
4288{
4289 int access = 0;
4290 if (bindingType == loadTypeVal) {
4291 access = QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePassState::Read;
4292 } else {
4293 access = QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePassState::Write;
4294 if (bindingType == loadStoreTypeVal)
4295 access |= QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePassState::Read;
4296 }
4297 auto it = writtenResources->find(resource);
4298 if (it != writtenResources->end())
4299 it->first |= access;
4300 else if (bindingType == storeTypeVal || bindingType == loadStoreTypeVal)
4301 writtenResources->insert(resource, { access, true });
4302}
4303
4304void QRhiGles2::dispatch(QRhiCommandBuffer *cb, int x, int y, int z)
4305{
4306 QGles2CommandBuffer *cbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2CommandBuffer, cb);
4307 Q_ASSERT(cbD->recordingPass == QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePass);
4308
4309 if (cbD->currentComputeSrb) {
4310 GLbitfield barriers = 0;
4311
4312 // The key in the writtenResources map indicates that the resource was
4313 // written in a previous dispatch, whereas the value accumulates the
4314 // access mask in the current one.
4315 for (auto &accessAndIsNewFlag : cbD->computePassState.writtenResources)
4316 accessAndIsNewFlag = { 0, false };
4317
4318 QGles2ShaderResourceBindings *srbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2ShaderResourceBindings, cbD->currentComputeSrb);
4319 const int bindingCount = srbD->m_bindings.size();
4320 for (int i = 0; i < bindingCount; ++i) {
4321 const QRhiShaderResourceBinding::Data *b = srbD->m_bindings.at(idx: i).data();
4322 switch (b->type) {
4323 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad:
4324 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore:
4325 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoadStore:
4326 qrhigl_accumulateComputeResource(writtenResources: &cbD->computePassState.writtenResources,
4327 resource: b->u.simage.tex,
4328 bindingType: b->type,
4329 loadTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoad,
4330 storeTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageStore,
4331 loadStoreTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::ImageLoadStore);
4332 break;
4333 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoad:
4334 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferStore:
4335 case QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoadStore:
4336 qrhigl_accumulateComputeResource(writtenResources: &cbD->computePassState.writtenResources,
4337 resource: b->u.sbuf.buf,
4338 bindingType: b->type,
4339 loadTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoad,
4340 storeTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferStore,
4341 loadStoreTypeVal: QRhiShaderResourceBinding::BufferLoadStore);
4342 break;
4343 default:
4344 break;
4345 }
4346 }
4347
4348 for (auto it = cbD->computePassState.writtenResources.begin(); it != cbD->computePassState.writtenResources.end(); ) {
4349 const int accessInThisDispatch = it->first;
4350 const bool isNewInThisDispatch = it->second;
4351 if (accessInThisDispatch && !isNewInThisDispatch) {
4352 if (it.key()->resourceType() == QRhiResource::Texture)
4353 barriers |= GL_SHADER_IMAGE_ACCESS_BARRIER_BIT;
4354 else
4355 barriers |= GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BARRIER_BIT;
4356 }
4357 // Anything that was previously written, but is only read now, can be
4358 // removed from the written list (because that previous write got a
4359 // corresponding barrier now).
4360 if (accessInThisDispatch == QGles2CommandBuffer::ComputePassState::Read)
4361 it = cbD->computePassState.writtenResources.erase(it);
4362 else
4363 ++it;
4364 }
4365
4366 if (barriers) {
4367 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
4368 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Barrier;
4369 cmd.args.barrier.barriers = barriers;
4370 }
4371 }
4372
4373 QGles2CommandBuffer::Command &cmd(cbD->commands.get());
4374 cmd.cmd = QGles2CommandBuffer::Command::Dispatch;
4375 cmd.args.dispatch.x = GLuint(x);
4376 cmd.args.dispatch.y = GLuint(y);
4377 cmd.args.dispatch.z = GLuint(z);
4378}

4400QByteArray QRhiGles2::shaderSource(const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage, QShaderVersion *shaderVersion)
4401{
4402 const QShader bakedShader = shaderStage.shader();
4403 QList<int> versionsToTry;
4404 QByteArray source;
4405 if (caps.gles) {
4406 if (caps.ctxMajor > 3 || (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor >= 2)) {
4407 versionsToTry << 320 << 310 << 300 << 100;
4408 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 1) {
4409 versionsToTry << 310 << 300 << 100;
4410 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 0) {
4411 versionsToTry << 300 << 100;
4412 } else {
4413 versionsToTry << 100;
4414 }
4415 for (int v : versionsToTry) {
4416 QShaderVersion ver(v, QShaderVersion::GlslEs);
4417 source = bakedShader.shader(key: { QShader::GlslShader, ver, shaderStage.shaderVariant() }).shader();
4418 if (!source.isEmpty()) {
4419 if (shaderVersion)
4420 *shaderVersion = ver;
4421 break;
4422 }
4423 }
4424 } else {
4425 if (caps.ctxMajor > 4 || (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor >= 6)) {
4426 versionsToTry << 460 << 450 << 440 << 430 << 420 << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4427 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 5) {
4428 versionsToTry << 450 << 440 << 430 << 420 << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4429 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 4) {
4430 versionsToTry << 440 << 430 << 420 << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4431 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 3) {
4432 versionsToTry << 430 << 420 << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4433 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 2) {
4434 versionsToTry << 420 << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4435 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 1) {
4436 versionsToTry << 410 << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4437 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 4 && caps.ctxMinor == 0) {
4438 versionsToTry << 400 << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4439 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 3) {
4440 versionsToTry << 330 << 150 << 140 << 130;
4441 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 2) {
4442 versionsToTry << 150 << 140 << 130;
4443 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 1) {
4444 versionsToTry << 140 << 130;
4445 } else if (caps.ctxMajor == 3 && caps.ctxMinor == 0) {
4446 versionsToTry << 130;
4447 }
4448 if (!caps.coreProfile)
4449 versionsToTry << 120;
4450 for (int v : versionsToTry) {
4451 source = bakedShader.shader(key: { QShader::GlslShader, v, shaderStage.shaderVariant() }).shader();
4452 if (!source.isEmpty()) {
4453 if (shaderVersion)
4454 *shaderVersion = v;
4455 break;
4456 }
4457 }
4458 }
4459 if (source.isEmpty()) {
4460 qWarning() << "No GLSL shader code found (versions tried: " << versionsToTry
4461 << ") in baked shader" << bakedShader;
4462 }
4463 return source;
4464}

4466bool QRhiGles2::compileShader(GLuint program, const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage, QShaderVersion *shaderVersion)
4467{
4468 const QByteArray source = shaderSource(shaderStage, shaderVersion);
4469 if (source.isEmpty())
4470 return false;
4471
4472 GLuint shader;
4473 auto cacheIt = m_shaderCache.constFind(key: shaderStage);
4474 if (cacheIt != m_shaderCache.constEnd()) {
4475 shader = *cacheIt;
4476 } else {
4477 shader = f->glCreateShader(type: toGlShaderType(type: shaderStage.type()));
4478 const char *srcStr = source.constData();
4479 const GLint srcLength = source.size();
4480 f->glShaderSource(shader, count: 1, string: &srcStr, length: &srcLength);
4481 f->glCompileShader(shader);
4482 GLint compiled = 0;
4483 f->glGetShaderiv(shader, GL_COMPILE_STATUS, params: &compiled);
4484 if (!compiled) {
4485 GLint infoLogLength = 0;
4486 f->glGetShaderiv(shader, GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH, params: &infoLogLength);
4487 QByteArray log;
4488 if (infoLogLength > 1) {
4489 GLsizei length = 0;
4490 log.resize(size: infoLogLength);
4491 f->glGetShaderInfoLog(shader, bufsize: infoLogLength, length: &length, infolog: log.data());
4492 }
4493 qWarning(msg: "Failed to compile shader: %s\nSource was:\n%s", log.constData(), source.constData());
4494 return false;
4495 }
4496 if (m_shaderCache.size() >= MAX_SHADER_CACHE_ENTRIES) {
4497 // Use the simplest strategy: too many cached shaders -> drop them all.
4498 for (uint shader : m_shaderCache)
4499 f->glDeleteShader(shader); // does not actually get released yet when attached to a not-yet-released program
4500 m_shaderCache.clear();
4501 }
4502 m_shaderCache.insert(key: shaderStage, value: shader);
4503 }
4504
4505 f->glAttachShader(program, shader);
4506
4507 return true;
4508}

4512 f->glLinkProgram(program);
4513 GLint linked = 0;
4514 f->glGetProgramiv(program, GL_LINK_STATUS, params: &linked);
4515 if (!linked) {
4516 GLint infoLogLength = 0;

4518 QByteArray log;
4519 if (infoLogLength > 1) {
4520 GLsizei length = 0;
4521 log.resize(size: infoLogLength);

4523 }

4525 return false;
4526 }

4529
4530void QRhiGles2::registerUniformIfActive(const QShaderDescription::BlockVariable &var,
4531 const QByteArray &namePrefix,
4532 int binding,
4533 int baseOffset,
4534 GLuint program,
4535 QDuplicateTracker<int, 256> *activeUniformLocations,
4536 QGles2UniformDescriptionVector *dst)
4537{
4538 if (var.type == QShaderDescription::Struct) {
4539 qWarning(msg: "Nested structs are not supported at the moment. '%s' ignored.",
4540 var.name.constData());
4541 return;
4542 }
4543 QGles2UniformDescription uniform;
4544 uniform.type = var.type;
4545 const QByteArray name = namePrefix + var.name;
4546 // Here we expect that the OpenGL implementation has proper active uniform
4547 // handling, meaning that a uniform that is declared but not accessed
4548 // elsewhere in the code is reported as -1 when querying the location. If
4549 // that is not the case, it won't break anything, but we'll generate
4550 // unnecessary glUniform* calls then.
4551 uniform.glslLocation = f->glGetUniformLocation(program, name: name.constData());
4552 if (uniform.glslLocation >= 0 && !activeUniformLocations->hasSeen(s: uniform.glslLocation)) {
4553 if (var.arrayDims.size() > 1) {
4554 qWarning(msg: "Array '%s' has more than one dimension. This is not supported.",
4555 var.name.constData());
4556 return;
4557 }
4558 uniform.binding = binding;
4559 uniform.offset = uint(baseOffset + var.offset);
4560 uniform.size = var.size;
4561 uniform.arrayDim = var.arrayDims.isEmpty() ? 0 : var.arrayDims.first();
4562 dst->append(t: uniform);
4563 }
4564}
4565
4566void QRhiGles2::gatherUniforms(GLuint program,
4567 const QShaderDescription::UniformBlock &ub,
4568 QDuplicateTracker<int, 256> *activeUniformLocations,
4569 QGles2UniformDescriptionVector *dst)
4570{
4571 QByteArray prefix = ub.structName + '.';
4572 for (const QShaderDescription::BlockVariable &blockMember : ub.members) {
4573 if (blockMember.type == QShaderDescription::Struct) {
4574 QByteArray structPrefix = prefix + blockMember.name;
4575
4576 const int baseOffset = blockMember.offset;
4577 if (blockMember.arrayDims.isEmpty()) {
4578 for (const QShaderDescription::BlockVariable &structMember : blockMember.structMembers)
4579 registerUniformIfActive(var: structMember, namePrefix: structPrefix + ".", binding: ub.binding,
4580 baseOffset, program, activeUniformLocations, dst);
4581 } else {
4582 if (blockMember.arrayDims.size() > 1) {
4583 qWarning(msg: "Array of struct '%s' has more than one dimension. Only the first "
4584 "dimension is used.",
4585 blockMember.name.constData());
4586 }
4587 const int dim = blockMember.arrayDims.first();
4588 const int elemSize = blockMember.size / dim;
4589 int elemOffset = baseOffset;
4590 for (int di = 0; di < dim; ++di) {
4591 const QByteArray arrayPrefix = structPrefix + '[' + QByteArray::number(di) + ']' + '.';
4592 for (const QShaderDescription::BlockVariable &structMember : blockMember.structMembers)
4593 registerUniformIfActive(var: structMember, namePrefix: arrayPrefix, binding: ub.binding, baseOffset: elemOffset, program, activeUniformLocations, dst);
4594 elemOffset += elemSize;
4595 }
4596 }
4597 } else {
4598 registerUniformIfActive(var: blockMember, namePrefix: prefix, binding: ub.binding, baseOffset: 0, program, activeUniformLocations, dst);
4599 }
4600 }
4601}

4631void QRhiGles2::sanityCheckVertexFragmentInterface(const QShaderDescription &vsDesc, const QShaderDescription &fsDesc)
4632{
4633 if (!vsDesc.isValid() || !fsDesc.isValid())
4634 return;
4635
4636 // Print a warning if the fragment shader input for a given location uses a
4637 // name that does not match the vertex shader output at the same location.
4638 // This is not an error with any other API and not with GLSL >= 330 either,
4639 // but matters for older GLSL code that has no location qualifiers.
4640 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &outVar : vsDesc.outputVariables()) {
4641 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &inVar : fsDesc.inputVariables()) {
4642 if (inVar.location == outVar.location) {
4643 if (inVar.name != outVar.name) {
4644 qWarning(msg: "Vertex output name '%s' does not match fragment input '%s'. "
4645 "This should be avoided because it causes problems with older GLSL versions.",
4646 outVar.name.constData(), inVar.name.constData());
4647 }
4648 break;
4649 }
4650 }
4651 }

4681
4682QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheResult QRhiGles2::tryLoadFromDiskOrPipelineCache(const QRhiShaderStage *stages,
4683 int stageCount,
4684 GLuint program,
4685 const QVector<QShaderDescription::InOutVariable> &inputVars,
4686 QByteArray *cacheKey)
4687{
4688 Q_ASSERT(cacheKey);
4689
4690 // the traditional QOpenGL disk cache since Qt 5.9
4691 const bool legacyDiskCacheEnabled = isProgramBinaryDiskCacheEnabled();
4692
4693 // QRhi's own (set)PipelineCacheData()
4694 const bool pipelineCacheEnabled = caps.programBinary && !m_pipelineCache.isEmpty();
4695
4696 // calculating the cache key based on the source code is common for both types of caches
4697 if (legacyDiskCacheEnabled || pipelineCacheEnabled) {
4698 QOpenGLProgramBinaryCache::ProgramDesc binaryProgram;
4699 for (int i = 0; i < stageCount; ++i) {
4700 const QRhiShaderStage &stage(stages[i]);
4701 QByteArray source = shaderSource(shaderStage: stage, shaderVersion: nullptr);
4702 if (source.isEmpty())
4703 return QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheError;
4704
4705 if (stage.type() == QRhiShaderStage::Vertex) {
4706 // Now add something to the key that indicates the vertex input locations.
4707 // A GLSL shader lower than 330 (150, 140, ...) will not have location
4708 // qualifiers. This means that the shader source code is the same
4709 // regardless of what locations inputVars contains. This becomes a problem
4710 // because we'll glBindAttribLocation the shader based on inputVars, but
4711 // that's only when compiling/linking when there was no cache hit. Picking
4712 // from the cache afterwards should take the input locations into account
4713 // since if inputVars has now different locations for the attributes, then
4714 // it is not ok to reuse a program binary that used different attribute
4715 // locations. For a lot of clients this would not be an issue since they
4716 // typically hardcode and use the same vertex locations on every run. Some
4717 // systems that dynamically generate shaders may end up with a non-stable
4718 // order (and so location numbers), however. This is sub-optimal because
4719 // it makes caching inefficient, and said clients should be fixed, but in
4720 // any case this should not break rendering. Hence including the locations
4721 // in the cache key.
4722 QMap<QByteArray, int> inputLocations; // sorted by key when iterating
4723 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &var : inputVars)
4724 inputLocations.insert(key: var.name, value: var.location);
4725 source += QByteArrayLiteral("\n // "); // just to be nice; treated as an arbitrary string regardless
4726 for (auto it = inputLocations.cbegin(), end = inputLocations.cend(); it != end; ++it) {
4727 source += it.key();
4728 source += QByteArray::number(it.value());
4729 }
4730 source += QByteArrayLiteral("\n");
4731 }
4732
4733 binaryProgram.shaders.append(t: QOpenGLProgramBinaryCache::ShaderDesc(toShaderStage(type: stage.type()), source));
4734 }
4735
4736 *cacheKey = binaryProgram.cacheKey();
4737
4738 // Try our pipeline cache simulation first, if it got seeded with
4739 // setPipelineCacheData and there's a hit, then no need to go to the
4740 // filesystem at all.
4741 if (pipelineCacheEnabled) {
4742 auto it = m_pipelineCache.constFind(key: *cacheKey);
4743 if (it != m_pipelineCache.constEnd()) {
4744 GLenum err;
4745 for ( ; ; ) {
4746 err = f->glGetError();
4747 if (err == GL_NO_ERROR || err == GL_CONTEXT_LOST)
4748 break;
4749 }
4750 f->glProgramBinary(program, binaryFormat: it->format, binary: it->data.constData(), length: it->data.size());
4751 err = f->glGetError();
4752 if (err == GL_NO_ERROR) {
4753 GLint linkStatus = 0;
4754 f->glGetProgramiv(program, GL_LINK_STATUS, params: &linkStatus);
4755 if (linkStatus == GL_TRUE)
4756 return QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheHit;
4757 }
4758 }
4759 }
4760
4761 if (legacyDiskCacheEnabled && qrhi_programBinaryCache()->load(cacheKey: *cacheKey, programId: program)) {
4762 // use the logging category QOpenGLShaderProgram would
4763 qCDebug(lcOpenGLProgramDiskCache, "Program binary received from cache, program %u, key %s",
4764 program, cacheKey->constData());
4765 return QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheHit;
4766 }
4767 }
4768
4769 return QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheMiss;
4770}

4784void QRhiGles2::trySaveToPipelineCache(GLuint program, const QByteArray &cacheKey, bool force)

4874
4875char *QGles2Buffer::beginFullDynamicBufferUpdateForCurrentFrame()
4876{
4877 Q_ASSERT(m_type == Dynamic);
4878 if (!m_usage.testFlag(flag: UniformBuffer)) {
4879 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
4880 rhiD->f->glBindBuffer(target: targetForDataOps, buffer);
4881 if (rhiD->caps.properMapBuffer) {
4882 return static_cast<char *>(rhiD->f->glMapBufferRange(target: targetForDataOps, offset: 0, length: nonZeroSize,
4883 GL_MAP_READ_BIT | GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT));
4884 } else {
4885 // Need some storage for the data, use the otherwise unused 'data' member.
4886 if (data.isEmpty())
4887 data.resize(size: nonZeroSize);
4888 }
4889 }
4890 return data.data();
4891}

4937
4938bool QGles2RenderBuffer::create()
4939{
4940 if (renderbuffer)
4941 destroy();
4942
4943 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
4944 samples = rhiD->effectiveSampleCount(sampleCount: m_sampleCount);
4945
4946 if (m_flags.testFlag(flag: UsedWithSwapChainOnly)) {
4947 if (m_type == DepthStencil)
4948 return true;
4949
4950 qWarning(msg: "RenderBuffer: UsedWithSwapChainOnly is meaningless in combination with Color");
4951 }
4952
4953 if (!rhiD->ensureContext())
4954 return false;
4955
4956 rhiD->f->glGenRenderbuffers(n: 1, renderbuffers: &renderbuffer);
4957 rhiD->f->glBindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbuffer);
4958
4959 const QSize size = m_pixelSize.isEmpty() ? QSize(1, 1) : m_pixelSize;
4960
4961 switch (m_type) {
4962 case QRhiRenderBuffer::DepthStencil:
4963 if (rhiD->caps.msaaRenderBuffer && samples > 1) {
4964 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorageMultisample(GL_RENDERBUFFER, samples, GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8,
4965 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
4966 stencilRenderbuffer = 0;
4967 } else if (rhiD->caps.packedDepthStencil || rhiD->caps.needsDepthStencilCombinedAttach) {
4968 const GLenum storage = rhiD->caps.needsDepthStencilCombinedAttach ? GL_DEPTH_STENCIL : GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8;
4969 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, internalformat: storage,
4970 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
4971 stencilRenderbuffer = 0;
4972 } else {
4973 GLenum depthStorage = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT;
4974 if (rhiD->caps.gles) {
4975 if (rhiD->caps.depth24)
4976 depthStorage = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24;
4977 else
4978 depthStorage = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT16; // plain ES 2.0 only has this
4979 }
4980 const GLenum stencilStorage = rhiD->caps.gles ? GL_STENCIL_INDEX8 : GL_STENCIL_INDEX;
4981 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, internalformat: depthStorage,
4982 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
4983 rhiD->f->glGenRenderbuffers(n: 1, renderbuffers: &stencilRenderbuffer);
4984 rhiD->f->glBindRenderbuffer(GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbuffer: stencilRenderbuffer);
4985 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, internalformat: stencilStorage,
4986 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
4987 }
4988 break;
4989 case QRhiRenderBuffer::Color:
4990 {
4991 GLenum internalFormat = GL_RGBA4; // ES 2.0
4992 if (rhiD->caps.rgba8Format) {
4993 internalFormat = GL_RGBA8;
4994 if (m_backingFormatHint != QRhiTexture::UnknownFormat) {
4995 GLenum glintformat, glformat, gltype;
4996 // only care about the sized internal format, the rest is not used here
4997 toGlTextureFormat(format: m_backingFormatHint, caps: rhiD->caps,
4998 glintformat: &glintformat, glsizedintformat: &internalFormat, glformat: &glformat, gltype: &gltype);
4999 }
5000 }
5001 if (rhiD->caps.msaaRenderBuffer && samples > 1) {
5002 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorageMultisample(GL_RENDERBUFFER, samples, internalformat: internalFormat,
5003 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
5004 } else {
5005 rhiD->f->glRenderbufferStorage(GL_RENDERBUFFER, internalformat: internalFormat,
5006 width: size.width(), height: size.height());
5007 }
5008 }
5009 break;
5010 default:
5011 Q_UNREACHABLE();
5012 break;
5013 }
5014
5015 owns = true;
5016 generation += 1;
5017 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
5018 return true;
5019}

5086
5087bool QGles2Texture::prepareCreate(QSize *adjustedSize)
5088{
5089 if (texture)
5090 destroy();
5091
5092 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
5093 if (!rhiD->ensureContext())
5094 return false;
5095
5096 const bool isCube = m_flags.testFlag(flag: CubeMap);
5097 const bool isArray = m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
5098 const bool is3D = m_flags.testFlag(flag: ThreeDimensional);
5099 const bool hasMipMaps = m_flags.testFlag(flag: MipMapped);
5100 const bool isCompressed = rhiD->isCompressedFormat(format: m_format);
5101 const bool is1D = m_flags.testFlag(flag: OneDimensional);
5102
5103 const QSize size = is1D ? QSize(qMax(a: 1, b: m_pixelSize.width()), 1)
5104 : (m_pixelSize.isEmpty() ? QSize(1, 1) : m_pixelSize);
5105
5106 if (is3D && !rhiD->caps.texture3D) {
5107 qWarning(msg: "3D textures are not supported");
5108 return false;
5109 }
5110 if (isCube && is3D) {
5111 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot be both cube and 3D");
5112 return false;
5113 }
5114 if (isArray && is3D) {
5115 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot be both array and 3D");
5116 return false;
5117 }
5118 if (is1D && !rhiD->caps.texture1D) {
5119 qWarning(msg: "1D textures are not supported");
5120 return false;
5121 }
5122 if (is1D && is3D) {
5123 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot be both 1D and 3D");
5124 return false;
5125 }
5126 if (is1D && isCube) {
5127 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot be both 1D and cube");
5128 return false;
5129 }
5130
5131 m_depth = qMax(a: 1, b: m_depth);
5132 if (m_depth > 1 && !is3D) {
5133 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot have a depth of %d when it is not 3D", m_depth);
5134 return false;
5135 }
5136 m_arraySize = qMax(a: 0, b: m_arraySize);
5137 if (m_arraySize > 0 && !isArray) {
5138 qWarning(msg: "Texture cannot have an array size of %d when it is not an array", m_arraySize);
5139 return false;
5140 }
5141 if (m_arraySize < 1 && isArray) {
5142 qWarning(msg: "Texture is an array but array size is %d", m_arraySize);
5143 return false;
5144 }
5145
5146 target = isCube ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP
5147 : m_sampleCount > 1 ? GL_TEXTURE_2D_MULTISAMPLE
5148 : (is3D ? GL_TEXTURE_3D
5149 : (is1D ? (isArray ? GL_TEXTURE_1D_ARRAY : GL_TEXTURE_1D)
5150 : (isArray ? GL_TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY : GL_TEXTURE_2D)));
5151
5152 if (m_flags.testFlag(flag: ExternalOES))
5153 target = GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL_OES;
5154 else if (m_flags.testFlag(flag: TextureRectangleGL))
5155 target = GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE;
5156
5157 mipLevelCount = hasMipMaps ? rhiD->q->mipLevelsForSize(size) : 1;
5158 gltype = GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE;
5159
5160 if (isCompressed) {
5161 if (m_flags.testFlag(flag: UsedWithLoadStore)) {
5162 qWarning(msg: "Compressed texture cannot be used with image load/store");
5163 return false;
5164 }
5165 glintformat = toGlCompressedTextureFormat(format: m_format, flags: m_flags);
5166 if (!glintformat) {
5167 qWarning(msg: "Compressed format %d not mappable to GL compressed format", m_format);
5168 return false;
5169 }
5170 glsizedintformat = glintformat;
5171 glformat = GL_RGBA;
5172 } else {
5173 toGlTextureFormat(format: m_format, caps: rhiD->caps,
5174 glintformat: &glintformat, glsizedintformat: &glsizedintformat, glformat: &glformat, gltype: &gltype);
5175 }
5176
5177 samplerState = QGles2SamplerData();
5178
5179 usageState.access = AccessNone;
5180
5181 if (adjustedSize)
5182 *adjustedSize = size;
5183
5184 return true;
5185}
5186
5187bool QGles2Texture::create()
5188{
5189 QSize size;
5190 if (!prepareCreate(adjustedSize: &size))
5191 return false;
5192
5193 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
5194 rhiD->f->glGenTextures(n: 1, textures: &texture);
5195
5196 const bool isCube = m_flags.testFlag(flag: CubeMap);
5197 const bool isArray = m_flags.testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray);
5198 const bool is3D = m_flags.testFlag(flag: ThreeDimensional);
5199 const bool hasMipMaps = m_flags.testFlag(flag: MipMapped);
5200 const bool isCompressed = rhiD->isCompressedFormat(format: m_format);
5201 const bool is1D = m_flags.testFlag(flag: OneDimensional);
5202
5203 if (!isCompressed) {
5204 rhiD->f->glBindTexture(target, texture);
5205 if (!m_flags.testFlag(flag: UsedWithLoadStore)) {
5206 if (is1D) {
5207 for (int level = 0; level < mipLevelCount; ++level) {
5208 const QSize mipSize = rhiD->q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: level, baseLevelSize: size);
5209 if (isArray)
5210 rhiD->f->glTexImage2D(target, level, internalformat: GLint(glintformat), width: mipSize.width(),
5211 height: m_arraySize, border: 0, format: glformat, type: gltype, pixels: nullptr);
5212 else
5213 rhiD->glTexImage1D(target, level, GLint(glintformat), mipSize.width(), 0,
5214 glformat, gltype, nullptr);
5215 }
5216 } else if (is3D || isArray) {
5217 const int layerCount = is3D ? m_depth : m_arraySize;
5218 if (hasMipMaps) {
5219 for (int level = 0; level != mipLevelCount; ++level) {
5220 const QSize mipSize = rhiD->q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: level, baseLevelSize: size);
5221 rhiD->f->glTexImage3D(target, level, internalformat: GLint(glintformat), width: mipSize.width(), height: mipSize.height(), depth: layerCount,
5222 border: 0, format: glformat, type: gltype, pixels: nullptr);
5223 }
5224 } else {
5225 rhiD->f->glTexImage3D(target, level: 0, internalformat: GLint(glintformat), width: size.width(), height: size.height(), depth: layerCount,
5226 border: 0, format: glformat, type: gltype, pixels: nullptr);
5227 }
5228 } else if (hasMipMaps || isCube) {
5229 const GLenum faceTargetBase = isCube ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X : target;
5230 for (int layer = 0, layerCount = isCube ? 6 : 1; layer != layerCount; ++layer) {
5231 for (int level = 0; level != mipLevelCount; ++level) {
5232 const QSize mipSize = rhiD->q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: level, baseLevelSize: size);
5233 rhiD->f->glTexImage2D(target: faceTargetBase + uint(layer), level, internalformat: GLint(glintformat),
5234 width: mipSize.width(), height: mipSize.height(), border: 0,
5235 format: glformat, type: gltype, pixels: nullptr);
5236 }
5237 }
5238 } else {
5239 rhiD->f->glTexImage2D(target, level: 0, internalformat: GLint(glintformat), width: size.width(), height: size.height(),
5240 border: 0, format: glformat, type: gltype, pixels: nullptr);
5241 }
5242 } else {
5243 // Must be specified with immutable storage functions otherwise
5244 // bindImageTexture may fail. Also, the internal format must be a
5245 // sized format here.
5246 if (is1D && !isArray)
5247 rhiD->glTexStorage1D(target, mipLevelCount, glsizedintformat, size.width());
5248 else if (!is1D && (is3D || isArray))
5249 rhiD->f->glTexStorage3D(target, levels: mipLevelCount, internalformat: glsizedintformat, width: size.width(), height: size.height(), depth: is3D ? m_depth : m_arraySize);
5250 else
5251 rhiD->f->glTexStorage2D(target, levels: mipLevelCount, internalformat: glsizedintformat, width: size.width(),
5252 height: is1D ? m_arraySize : size.height());
5253 }
5254 specified = true;
5255 } else {
5256 // Cannot use glCompressedTexImage2D without valid data, so defer.
5257 // Compressed textures will not be used as render targets so this is
5258 // not an issue.
5259 specified = false;
5260 }
5261
5262 owns = true;
5263
5264 generation += 1;
5265 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
5266 return true;
5267}

5423
5424bool QGles2TextureRenderTarget::create()
5425{
5426 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
5427
5428 if (framebuffer)
5429 destroy();
5430
5431 const bool hasColorAttachments = m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments() != m_desc.cendColorAttachments();
5432 Q_ASSERT(hasColorAttachments || m_desc.depthTexture());
5433 Q_ASSERT(!m_desc.depthStencilBuffer() || !m_desc.depthTexture());
5434 const bool hasDepthStencil = m_desc.depthStencilBuffer() || m_desc.depthTexture();
5435
5436 if (hasColorAttachments) {
5437 const int count = m_desc.cendColorAttachments() - m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments();
5438 if (count > rhiD->caps.maxDrawBuffers) {
5439 qWarning(msg: "QGles2TextureRenderTarget: Too many color attachments (%d, max is %d)",
5440 count, rhiD->caps.maxDrawBuffers);
5441 }
5442 }
5443 if (m_desc.depthTexture() && !rhiD->caps.depthTexture)
5444 qWarning(msg: "QGles2TextureRenderTarget: Depth texture is not supported and will be ignored");
5445
5446 if (!rhiD->ensureContext())
5447 return false;
5448
5449 rhiD->f->glGenFramebuffers(n: 1, framebuffers: &framebuffer);
5450 rhiD->f->glBindFramebuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, framebuffer);
5451
5452 d.colorAttCount = 0;
5453 int attIndex = 0;
5454 for (auto it = m_desc.cbeginColorAttachments(), itEnd = m_desc.cendColorAttachments(); it != itEnd; ++it, ++attIndex) {
5455 d.colorAttCount += 1;
5456 const QRhiColorAttachment &colorAtt(*it);
5457 QRhiTexture *texture = colorAtt.texture();
5458 QRhiRenderBuffer *renderBuffer = colorAtt.renderBuffer();
5459 Q_ASSERT(texture || renderBuffer);
5460 if (texture) {
5461 QGles2Texture *texD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, texture);
5462 Q_ASSERT(texD->texture && texD->specified);
5463 if (texD->flags().testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::ThreeDimensional) || texD->flags().testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::TextureArray)) {
5464 rhiD->f->glFramebufferTextureLayer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + uint(attIndex), texture: texD->texture,
5465 level: colorAtt.level(), layer: colorAtt.layer());
5466 } else if (texD->flags().testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::OneDimensional)) {
5467 rhiD->glFramebufferTexture1D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + uint(attIndex),
5468 texD->target + uint(colorAtt.layer()), texD->texture,
5469 colorAtt.level());
5470 } else {
5471 const GLenum faceTargetBase = texD->flags().testFlag(flag: QRhiTexture::CubeMap) ? GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X : texD->target;
5472 rhiD->f->glFramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + uint(attIndex), textarget: faceTargetBase + uint(colorAtt.layer()),
5473 texture: texD->texture, level: colorAtt.level());
5474 }
5475 if (attIndex == 0) {
5476 d.pixelSize = rhiD->q->sizeForMipLevel(mipLevel: colorAtt.level(), baseLevelSize: texD->pixelSize());
5477 d.sampleCount = 1;
5478 }
5479 } else if (renderBuffer) {
5480 QGles2RenderBuffer *rbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2RenderBuffer, renderBuffer);
5481 rhiD->f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + uint(attIndex), GL_RENDERBUFFER, renderbuffer: rbD->renderbuffer);
5482 if (attIndex == 0) {
5483 d.pixelSize = rbD->pixelSize();
5484 d.sampleCount = rbD->samples;
5485 }
5486 }
5487 }
5488
5489 if (hasDepthStencil) {
5490 if (m_desc.depthStencilBuffer()) {
5491 QGles2RenderBuffer *depthRbD = QRHI_RES(QGles2RenderBuffer, m_desc.depthStencilBuffer());
5492 if (rhiD->caps.needsDepthStencilCombinedAttach) {
5493 rhiD->f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER,
5494 renderbuffer: depthRbD->renderbuffer);
5495 } else {
5496 rhiD->f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER,
5497 renderbuffer: depthRbD->renderbuffer);
5498 if (depthRbD->stencilRenderbuffer)
5499 rhiD->f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER,
5500 renderbuffer: depthRbD->stencilRenderbuffer);
5501 else // packed
5502 rhiD->f->glFramebufferRenderbuffer(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT, GL_RENDERBUFFER,
5503 renderbuffer: depthRbD->renderbuffer);
5504 }
5505 if (d.colorAttCount == 0) {
5506 d.pixelSize = depthRbD->pixelSize();
5507 d.sampleCount = depthRbD->samples;
5508 }
5509 } else {
5510 QGles2Texture *depthTexD = QRHI_RES(QGles2Texture, m_desc.depthTexture());
5511 rhiD->f->glFramebufferTexture2D(GL_FRAMEBUFFER, GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, textarget: depthTexD->target,
5512 texture: depthTexD->texture, level: 0);
5513 if (d.colorAttCount == 0) {
5514 d.pixelSize = depthTexD->pixelSize();
5515 d.sampleCount = 1;
5516 }
5517 }
5518 d.dsAttCount = 1;
5519 } else {
5520 d.dsAttCount = 0;
5521 }
5522
5523 d.dpr = 1;
5524 d.rp = QRHI_RES(QGles2RenderPassDescriptor, m_renderPassDesc);
5525
5526 GLenum status = rhiD->f->glCheckFramebufferStatus(GL_FRAMEBUFFER);
5527 if (status != GL_NO_ERROR && status != GL_FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE) {
5528 qWarning(msg: "Framebuffer incomplete: 0x%x", status);
5529 return false;
5530 }
5531
5532 QRhiRenderTargetAttachmentTracker::updateResIdList<QGles2Texture, QGles2RenderBuffer>(desc: m_desc, dst: &d.currentResIdList);
5533
5534 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
5535 return true;
5536}

5631static inline bool isGraphicsStage(const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage)
5632{
5633 const QRhiShaderStage::Type t = shaderStage.type();
5634 return t == QRhiShaderStage::Vertex
5635 || t == QRhiShaderStage::TessellationControl
5636 || t == QRhiShaderStage::TessellationEvaluation
5637 || t == QRhiShaderStage::Geometry
5638 || t == QRhiShaderStage::Fragment;
5639}
5640
5641bool QGles2GraphicsPipeline::create()
5642{
5643 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
5644
5645 if (program)
5646 destroy();
5647
5648 if (!rhiD->ensureContext())
5649 return false;
5650
5651 rhiD->pipelineCreationStart();
5652 if (!rhiD->sanityCheckGraphicsPipeline(ps: this))
5653 return false;
5654
5655 drawMode = toGlTopology(t: m_topology);
5656
5657 program = rhiD->f->glCreateProgram();
5658
5659 enum {
5660 VtxIdx = 0,
5661 TCIdx,
5662 TEIdx,
5663 GeomIdx,
5664 FragIdx,
5665 LastIdx
5666 };
5667 const auto descIdxForStage = [](const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage) {
5668 switch (shaderStage.type()) {
5669 case QRhiShaderStage::Vertex:
5670 return VtxIdx;
5671 case QRhiShaderStage::TessellationControl:
5672 return TCIdx;
5673 case QRhiShaderStage::TessellationEvaluation:
5674 return TEIdx;
5675 case QRhiShaderStage::Geometry:
5676 return GeomIdx;
5677 case QRhiShaderStage::Fragment:
5678 return FragIdx;
5679 default:
5680 break;
5681 }
5682 Q_UNREACHABLE_RETURN(VtxIdx);
5683 };
5684 QShaderDescription desc[LastIdx];
5685 QShader::SeparateToCombinedImageSamplerMappingList samplerMappingList[LastIdx];
5686 bool vertexFragmentOnly = true;
5687 for (const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage : std::as_const(t&: m_shaderStages)) {
5688 if (isGraphicsStage(shaderStage)) {
5689 const int idx = descIdxForStage(shaderStage);
5690 if (idx != VtxIdx && idx != FragIdx)
5691 vertexFragmentOnly = false;
5692 QShader shader = shaderStage.shader();
5693 QShaderVersion shaderVersion;
5694 desc[idx] = shader.description();
5695 if (!rhiD->shaderSource(shaderStage, shaderVersion: &shaderVersion).isEmpty()) {
5696 samplerMappingList[idx] = shader.separateToCombinedImageSamplerMappingList(
5697 key: { QShader::GlslShader, shaderVersion, shaderStage.shaderVariant() });
5698 }
5699 }
5700 }
5701
5702 QByteArray cacheKey;
5703 QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheResult cacheResult = rhiD->tryLoadFromDiskOrPipelineCache(stages: m_shaderStages.constData(),
5704 stageCount: m_shaderStages.size(),
5705 program,
5706 inputVars: desc[VtxIdx].inputVariables(),
5707 cacheKey: &cacheKey);
5708 if (cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheError)
5709 return false;
5710
5711 if (cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheMiss) {
5712 for (const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage : std::as_const(t&: m_shaderStages)) {
5713 if (isGraphicsStage(shaderStage)) {
5714 if (!rhiD->compileShader(program, shaderStage, shaderVersion: nullptr))
5715 return false;
5716 }
5717 }
5718
5719 // important when GLSL <= 150 is used that does not have location qualifiers
5720 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &inVar : desc[VtxIdx].inputVariables())
5721 rhiD->f->glBindAttribLocation(program, index: GLuint(inVar.location), name: inVar.name);
5722
5723 if (vertexFragmentOnly)
5724 rhiD->sanityCheckVertexFragmentInterface(vsDesc: desc[VtxIdx], fsDesc: desc[FragIdx]);
5725
5726 if (!rhiD->linkProgram(program))
5727 return false;
5728
5729 if (rhiD->rhiFlags.testFlag(flag: QRhi::EnablePipelineCacheDataSave)) {
5730 // force replacing existing cache entry (if there is one, then
5731 // something is wrong with it, as there was no hit)
5732 rhiD->trySaveToPipelineCache(program, cacheKey, force: true);
5733 } else {
5734 // legacy QOpenGLShaderProgram style behavior: the "pipeline cache"
5735 // was not enabled, so instead store to the Qt 5 disk cache
5736 rhiD->trySaveToDiskCache(program, cacheKey);
5737 }
5738 } else {
5739 Q_ASSERT(cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheHit);
5740 if (rhiD->rhiFlags.testFlag(flag: QRhi::EnablePipelineCacheDataSave)) {
5741 // just so that it ends up in the pipeline cache also when the hit was
5742 // from the disk cache
5743 rhiD->trySaveToPipelineCache(program, cacheKey);
5744 }
5745 }
5746
5747 // Use the same work area for the vertex & fragment stages, thus ensuring
5748 // that we will not do superfluous glUniform calls for uniforms that are
5749 // present in both shaders.
5750 QDuplicateTracker<int, 256> activeUniformLocations;
5751
5752 for (const QRhiShaderStage &shaderStage : std::as_const(t&: m_shaderStages)) {
5753 if (isGraphicsStage(shaderStage)) {
5754 const int idx = descIdxForStage(shaderStage);
5755 for (const QShaderDescription::UniformBlock &ub : desc[idx].uniformBlocks())
5756 rhiD->gatherUniforms(program, ub, activeUniformLocations: &activeUniformLocations, dst: &uniforms);
5757 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &v : desc[idx].combinedImageSamplers())
5758 rhiD->gatherSamplers(program, v, dst: &samplers);
5759 for (const QShader::SeparateToCombinedImageSamplerMapping &mapping : samplerMappingList[idx])
5760 rhiD->gatherGeneratedSamplers(program, mapping, dst: &samplers);
5761 }
5762 }
5763
5764 std::sort(first: uniforms.begin(), last: uniforms.end(),
5765 comp: [](const QGles2UniformDescription &a, const QGles2UniformDescription &b)
5766 {
5767 return a.offset < b.offset;
5768 });
5769
5770 memset(s: uniformState, c: 0, n: sizeof(uniformState));
5771
5772 currentSrb = nullptr;
5773 currentSrbGeneration = 0;
5774
5775 rhiD->pipelineCreationEnd();
5776 generation += 1;
5777 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
5778 return true;
5779}

5812bool QGles2ComputePipeline::create()
5813{
5814 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
5815
5816 if (program)
5817 destroy();
5818
5819 if (!rhiD->ensureContext())
5820 return false;
5821
5822 rhiD->pipelineCreationStart();
5823
5824 const QShaderDescription csDesc = m_shaderStage.shader().description();
5825 QShader::SeparateToCombinedImageSamplerMappingList csSamplerMappingList;
5826 QShaderVersion shaderVersion;
5827 if (!rhiD->shaderSource(shaderStage: m_shaderStage, shaderVersion: &shaderVersion).isEmpty()) {
5828 csSamplerMappingList = m_shaderStage.shader().separateToCombinedImageSamplerMappingList(
5829 key: { QShader::GlslShader, shaderVersion, m_shaderStage.shaderVariant() });
5830 }
5831
5832 program = rhiD->f->glCreateProgram();
5833
5834 QByteArray cacheKey;
5835 QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheResult cacheResult = rhiD->tryLoadFromDiskOrPipelineCache(stages: &m_shaderStage, stageCount: 1, program, inputVars: {}, cacheKey: &cacheKey);
5836 if (cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheError)
5837 return false;
5838
5839 if (cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheMiss) {
5840 if (!rhiD->compileShader(program, shaderStage: m_shaderStage, shaderVersion: nullptr))
5841 return false;
5842
5843 if (!rhiD->linkProgram(program))
5844 return false;
5845
5846 if (rhiD->rhiFlags.testFlag(flag: QRhi::EnablePipelineCacheDataSave)) {
5847 // force replacing existing cache entry (if there is one, then
5848 // something is wrong with it, as there was no hit)
5849 rhiD->trySaveToPipelineCache(program, cacheKey, force: true);
5850 } else {
5851 // legacy QOpenGLShaderProgram style behavior: the "pipeline cache"
5852 // was not enabled, so instead store to the Qt 5 disk cache
5853 rhiD->trySaveToDiskCache(program, cacheKey);
5854 }
5855 } else {
5856 Q_ASSERT(cacheResult == QRhiGles2::ProgramCacheHit);
5857 if (rhiD->rhiFlags.testFlag(flag: QRhi::EnablePipelineCacheDataSave)) {
5858 // just so that it ends up in the pipeline cache also when the hit was
5859 // from the disk cache
5860 rhiD->trySaveToPipelineCache(program, cacheKey);
5861 }
5862 }
5863
5864 QDuplicateTracker<int, 256> activeUniformLocations;
5865 for (const QShaderDescription::UniformBlock &ub : csDesc.uniformBlocks())
5866 rhiD->gatherUniforms(program, ub, activeUniformLocations: &activeUniformLocations, dst: &uniforms);
5867 for (const QShaderDescription::InOutVariable &v : csDesc.combinedImageSamplers())
5868 rhiD->gatherSamplers(program, v, dst: &samplers);
5869 for (const QShader::SeparateToCombinedImageSamplerMapping &mapping : csSamplerMappingList)
5870 rhiD->gatherGeneratedSamplers(program, mapping, dst: &samplers);
5871
5872 // storage images and buffers need no special steps here
5873
5874 memset(s: uniformState, c: 0, n: sizeof(uniformState));
5875
5876 currentSrb = nullptr;
5877 currentSrbGeneration = 0;
5878
5879 rhiD->pipelineCreationEnd();
5880 generation += 1;
5881 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
5882 return true;
5883}

5969
5970bool QGles2SwapChain::createOrResize()
5971{
5972 // can be called multiple times due to window resizes
5973 const bool needsRegistration = !surface || surface != m_window;
5974 if (surface && surface != m_window)
5975 destroy();
5976
5977 surface = m_window;
5978 m_currentPixelSize = surfacePixelSize();
5979 pixelSize = m_currentPixelSize;
5980
5981 if (m_depthStencil && m_depthStencil->flags().testFlag(flag: QRhiRenderBuffer::UsedWithSwapChainOnly)
5982 && m_depthStencil->pixelSize() != pixelSize)
5983 {
5984 m_depthStencil->setPixelSize(pixelSize);
5985 m_depthStencil->create();
5986 }
5987
5988 initSwapChainRenderTarget(rt: &rt);
5989
5990 if (m_window->format().stereo()) {
5991 initSwapChainRenderTarget(rt: &rtLeft);
5992 rtLeft.d.stereoTarget = QRhiSwapChain::LeftBuffer;
5993 initSwapChainRenderTarget(rt: &rtRight);
5994 rtRight.d.stereoTarget = QRhiSwapChain::RightBuffer;
5995 }
5996
5997 frameCount = 0;
5998
5999 // The only reason to register this fairly fake gl swapchain
6000 // object with no native resources underneath is to be able to
6001 // implement a safe destroy().
6002 if (needsRegistration) {
6003 QRHI_RES_RHI(QRhiGles2);
6004 rhiD->registerResource(res: this);
6005 }
6006
6007 return true;
6008}
